I was a war baby.</i>

18
00:02:03,466 --> 00:02:05,432
<i>But luckily for me, I haven't had to fight...</i>

19
00:02:05,533 --> 00:02:09,932
<i>in any of the 165 wars
that have occurred in my lifetime.</i>

20
00:02:10,967 --> 00:02:13,330
<i>My father wasn't so lucky.</i>

21
00:02:14,633 --> 00:02:16,259
<i>When he was a young man...</i>

22
00:02:16,367 --> 00:02:19,560
<i>everyone in Spain had
to take sides and take up arms.</i>

23
00:02:20,667 --> 00:02:23,065
<i>The decision may have taken a second...</i>

24
00:02:23,167 --> 00:02:26,531
<i>but the consequences
lasted the rest of his life.</i>

25
00:02:27,833 --> 00:02:30,425
<i>He never talked about the war...</i>

26
00:02:30,534 --> 00:02:34,057
<i>until I was asked to write a book
about a dead priest-</i>

27
00:02:34,167 --> 00:02:36,360
<i>Josemaría Escrivá.</i>

28
00:02:36,467 --> 00:02:40,695
<i>And then he began to talk and talk and talk.</i>

29
00:02:43,068 --> 00:02:47,363
<i>And that's how I went looking for a saint
and found my father instead.</i>

30
00:02:50,668 --> 00:02:53,600
<i>I think it was Oscar Wilde who wrote...</i>

31
00:02:53,701 --> 00:02:55,894
<i>"Every saint has a past...</i>

32
00:02:56,001 --> 00:02:59,058
<i>and every sinner has a future. "</i>

33
00:03:06,302 --> 00:03:07,359
Josemaría!

34
00:03:07,468 --> 00:03:09,559
It's the Father. Quick!

35
00:03:09,669 --> 00:03:11,635
Quick! Get the doctor!

36
00:03:22,969 --> 00:03:25,867
<i>[Wind Howling]</i>

37
00:03:31,536 --> 00:03:33,559
[Man]
In June of 1976...

38
00:03:33,669 --> 00:03:36,135
the nun was at the point of death...

39
00:03:36,236 --> 00:03:41,669
diagnosed with a multiple
calcific lipomatosis tumor, causing pain...

40
00:03:41,770 --> 00:03:47,327
attaining a mass the size of an orange
on the left shoulder.

41
00:03:47,436 --> 00:03:51,198
Cured in a sudden and lasting way...

42
00:03:51,303 --> 00:03:57,203
after the Servant of God,
Josemaría Escrivá...

43
00:03:57,303 --> 00:03:59,997
had been invoked.

44
00:04:03,903 --> 00:04:05,892
[Phone Ringing]

45
00:04:07,370 --> 00:04:09,733
- [Ringing]
- [Machine Clicks, Beeps]

46
00:04:09,836 --> 00:04:12,234
<i>[Man]
You have reached Judge Manolo Torres.</i>

47
00:04:12,337 --> 00:04:15,428
<i>- Leave a message.
- [Beeps]</i>

48
00:04:15,537 --> 00:04:19,560
<i>Dad? It's- It's me, Robert.</i>

49
00:04:19,671 --> 00:04:21,432
<i>Your son.</i>

50
00:04:21,537 --> 00:04:23,230
<i>I'm in Rome.</i>

51
00:04:23,337 --> 00:04:25,895
<i>I'm doing a book on Josemaría Escrivá.</i>

52
00:04:26,871 --> 00:04:29,428
<i>I'm- I'm coming to Madrid, Dad...</i>

53
00:04:29,537 --> 00:04:33,367
<i>and, you know, I-I want
to talk to you about him.</i>

54
00:04:33,470 --> 00:04:34,868
<i>Are you there?</i>

55
00:04:34,971 --> 00:04:37,766
<i>Please, Dad, pick up the phone.</i>

56
00:04:39,871 --> 00:04:43,065
<i>Okay. Well, I'll call you when I arrive.</i>

57
00:04:43,171 --> 00:04:44,864
[Machine Clicks]

58
00:04:47,538 --> 00:04:50,163
And why this interest in Escrivá?

59
00:04:50,271 --> 00:04:55,898
The uproar in the press about his possible
canonization turned my publisher on.

60
00:04:57,171 --> 00:04:59,797
You know, and curiously, he-

61
00:04:59,905 --> 00:05:02,427
he came from the same town as my father.

62
00:05:02,538 --> 00:05:06,198
Ah, yes, of course.
How is the judge, Roberto?

63
00:05:06,305 --> 00:05:08,567
To be honest, l-
[Clears Throat]

64
00:05:08,672 --> 00:05:10,570
We haven't spoken in...

65
00:05:10,672 --> 00:05:12,433
eight years.

66
00:05:14,039 --> 00:05:17,233
So I moved to London permanently,
and since then-

67
00:05:17,339 --> 00:05:20,032
Well, he's not very forgiving,
my father.

68
00:05:20,139 --> 00:05:21,605
Eight years, huh?

69
00:05:21,705 --> 00:05:23,695
- Children?
- No.

70
00:05:23,805 --> 00:05:25,930
I don't quite see myself as a father.

71
00:05:26,039 --> 00:05:27,403
[Chuckles]

72
00:05:27,506 --> 00:05:29,665
Your father is a product of difficult times.

73
00:05:29,773 --> 00:05:31,739
You should try to understand him.

74
00:05:31,839 --> 00:05:34,430
Well, I do, Monsignor. I do.

75
00:05:34,539 --> 00:05:36,971
God bless you in your quest.

76
00:05:37,073 --> 00:05:39,538
- And give my regards to, uh-
- To Leila.

77
00:05:39,639 --> 00:05:41,605
Leila.

78
00:05:41,706 --> 00:05:43,535
- Good-bye.
- Good-bye.

79
00:05:50,906 --> 00:05:53,134
- [Robert] Are you sure?
- Yes.

80
00:05:54,273 --> 00:05:57,796
That's Josemaría Escrivá in the middle.

81
00:05:57,906 --> 00:06:00,270
And that's me on the right.

82
00:06:00,373 --> 00:06:03,271
And on the left, your father.

83
00:06:04,407 --> 00:06:07,373
Here's another one. At the seminary.

84
00:06:08,707 --> 00:06:11,003
<i>- [Phone Rings]
- [Line Clicks]</i>

85
00:06:11,106 --> 00:06:12,538
<i>[Manolo]
Hello.</i>

86
00:06:12,640 --> 00:06:15,004
Dad. I'm in Madrid.

87
00:06:15,107 --> 00:06:16,538
Been a long time.

88
00:06:16,640 --> 00:06:21,039
Listen. I'm close to the apartment,
and I wanted to come see you.

89
00:06:21,141 --> 00:06:23,369
Why would you write a book about him?

90
00:06:23,473 --> 00:06:25,632
That's what I wanted to talk to you about.

91
00:06:25,740 --> 00:06:27,638
Leave it alone, Roberto.

92
00:06:27,740 --> 00:06:30,172
<i>Well, I found out that you were
in the seminary with him...</i>

93
00:06:30,274 --> 00:06:32,967
and you never told me
that you wanted to be a priest.

94
00:06:33,074 --> 00:06:36,438
<i>- Don't you think that's weird?
- Yes, I thought so too.</i>

95
00:06:36,541 --> 00:06:38,871
That's why I left after a year, Roberto.

96
00:06:38,974 --> 00:06:41,600
Why? Was it because of the civil war?

97
00:06:41,708 --> 00:06:43,401
<i>- [Gasps]
- [Line Clicks]</i>

98
00:06:43,508 --> 00:06:45,303
<i>[Dial Tone]</i>

99
00:06:59,175 --> 00:07:01,141
<i>[Woman]
Hello. London University.</i>

100
00:07:01,242 --> 00:07:03,538
Dr. Leila Azoulay, please.

101
00:07:03,641 --> 00:07:05,198
<i>Which department?</i>

102
00:07:05,309 --> 00:07:07,332
Mathematical Physics.

103
00:07:07,442 --> 00:07:09,964
Good timing.
I was just about to call you.

104
00:07:10,075 --> 00:07:11,701
<i>How's Spain?</i>

105
00:07:11,809 --> 00:07:13,206
I love Spain.

106
00:07:13,309 --> 00:07:15,366
<i>How's your father?</i>

107
00:07:15,475 --> 00:07:17,338
I love Spain.

108
00:07:19,342 --> 00:07:20,865
<i>Tell me.</i>

109
00:07:20,976 --> 00:07:23,999
He doesn't want me to do
this Josemaría Escrivá thing.

110
00:07:24,109 --> 00:07:26,597
At least you two spoke. That's progress, no?

111
00:07:26,709 --> 00:07:29,301
He knows something about Josemaría, damn it.

112
00:07:29,409 --> 00:07:33,035
I know he does. Why can't he just tell me?

113
00:07:33,143 --> 00:07:36,507
I could wrangle the weekend away.

114
00:07:36,609 --> 00:07:39,167
Want me to come out?

115
00:07:39,410 --> 00:07:41,273
[Hinges Squeak]

116
00:07:53,877 --> 00:07:55,342
[Woman Screams]

117
00:08:06,110 --> 00:08:08,473
[Grunting]

118
00:08:08,576 --> 00:08:10,701
[Sighs, Panting]
Gun.

119
00:08:21,877 --> 00:08:23,173
No!

120
00:08:25,678 --> 00:08:27,143
Damn it.

121
00:08:29,377 --> 00:08:30,502
[Groans]

122
00:08:31,811 --> 00:08:33,276
[Groans]

123
00:08:35,210 --> 00:08:38,143
[Groaning]

124
00:08:40,978 --> 00:08:43,171
[Keys Jingling]

125
00:08:43,278 --> 00:08:45,073
[Lock Clicks]

126
00:09:05,245 --> 00:09:07,768
[Clears Throat]

127
00:09:07,879 --> 00:09:12,538
I was nine
when Josemaría's path crossed mine.

128
00:09:13,712 --> 00:09:16,144
<i>A long time ago.</i>

129
00:09:16,246 --> 00:09:20,769
<i>Roberto, you've often told me
that I was a terrible father.</i>

130
00:09:20,879 --> 00:09:23,811
<i>What I've never told you
is that I agree with you.</i>

131
00:09:23,912 --> 00:09:27,867
<i>- Manolo! Manolo!
- There's so much I haven't
told you that you need to know.</i>

132
00:09:27,979 --> 00:09:30,537
<i>- So if you want to hear about the past...
- Manolo!</i>

133
00:09:30,646 --> 00:09:32,043
<i>- I'll tell you.
- Manolo!</i>

134
00:09:32,146 --> 00:09:36,169
<i>- But I warn you, there be dragons.
- Manolo! Manolo!</i>

135
00:09:36,279 --> 00:09:38,142
Are you okay? Manolo!

136
00:09:38,246 --> 00:09:39,644
- Manolo!
- [Shouts]

137
00:09:39,746 --> 00:09:41,541
[Gasps]
You got me.

138
00:09:41,646 --> 00:09:44,441
<i>- I got you, Josemaría.
- I was a little terror like most boys.</i>

139
00:09:44,546 --> 00:09:47,376
<i>- I'm gonna get you.
- Josemaría was no saint either.</i>

140
00:09:47,479 --> 00:09:49,707
<i>There was one day he almost killed me.</i>

141
00:09:49,813 --> 00:09:51,177
[Horse Whinnying]

142
00:09:51,980 --> 00:09:52,946
[Woman Shrieks]

143
00:09:53,047 --> 00:09:56,172
Good driving, boy. Come on!

144
00:09:56,280 --> 00:09:58,905
[Yelling]

145
00:09:59,013 --> 00:10:01,309
[Woman Shrieking]

146
00:10:01,414 --> 00:10:05,107
[Chattering]

147
00:10:12,814 --> 00:10:16,008
Feels like a Taurus, Manolo.
Faster!

148
00:10:19,981 --> 00:10:20,969
[Screams]

149
00:10:24,081 --> 00:10:25,808
Stop!

150
00:10:25,914 --> 00:10:28,937
- Manolo, are you all right?
- Are you mad?

151
00:10:29,048 --> 00:10:32,503
Josemaría, I'll speak to your father.
He should give you a beating.

152
00:10:32,614 --> 00:10:35,206
<i>I hate this backwater.</i>

153
00:10:35,315 --> 00:10:38,838
I've half a mind to sell up
and go back to Madrid, I promise.

154
00:10:40,315 --> 00:10:43,213
- Can I drive again, Papa?
- No, Manolo. Enough.

155
00:10:53,982 --> 00:10:56,277
[Children Chattering, Laughing]

156
00:10:56,381 --> 00:10:59,041
[Barking]

157
00:11:01,581 --> 00:11:03,706
[Woman]
Here is the first one.

158
00:11:05,949 --> 00:11:07,381
See?

159
00:11:07,482 --> 00:11:11,073
There are many kinds of dragons
you will have to face.

160
00:11:11,182 --> 00:11:12,807
She scares me.

161
00:11:12,915 --> 00:11:15,473
Don't be scared, Manolo.

162
00:11:15,582 --> 00:11:18,480
How many dragons are there, Abileyza?

163
00:11:18,582 --> 00:11:20,343
Many, Josemaría.

164
00:11:20,449 --> 00:11:24,040
But what matters is how you face them,
as you shall see.

165
00:11:24,149 --> 00:11:27,582
<i>[Manolo Narrating]
Josemaría's nanny talked about dragons...</i>

166
00:11:27,683 --> 00:11:30,013
<i>as if they really existed.</i>

167
00:11:30,116 --> 00:11:35,048
<i>A quarter of a century passed
before I realized she was right.</i>

168
00:11:36,250 --> 00:11:38,875
<i>But things happened in Josemaría's life...</i>

169
00:11:38,983 --> 00:11:42,915
<i>that meant he understood this before I did.</i>

170
00:11:46,050 --> 00:11:49,414
[Woman Sobbing]
Why?

171
00:11:51,650 --> 00:11:53,979
No!

172
00:11:54,083 --> 00:11:55,981
No!

173
00:11:56,083 --> 00:11:59,049
[Sobbing Continues]

174
00:12:06,350 --> 00:12:08,816
My baby! Why?

175
00:12:41,318 --> 00:12:43,910
<i>[Manolo Narrating]
Josemaría lost three sisters.</i>

176
00:12:44,952 --> 00:12:47,383
<i>I lost a baby brother.</i>

177
00:12:47,484 --> 00:12:50,110
<i>In those days, death was part of life.</i>

178
00:13:02,319 --> 00:13:03,944
[Josemaría]
Mama?

179
00:13:04,985 --> 00:13:07,281
Do you hate God now?

180
00:13:07,385 --> 00:13:09,749
No, dearest.

181
00:13:14,752 --> 00:13:17,843
I... love him very much.

182
00:13:19,519 --> 00:13:21,849
Will you hate him when he takes me away?

183
00:13:23,986 --> 00:13:25,474
Come here.

184
00:13:44,186 --> 00:13:46,448
I'm sorry about your sister.

185
00:13:46,553 --> 00:13:50,849
<i>[Manolo Narrating]
Josemaría's father owned a chocolate factory.</i>

186
00:13:50,954 --> 00:13:54,216
<i>The manager was a strange, old guy-</i>

187
00:13:54,320 --> 00:13:55,786
<i>Honorio.</i>

188
00:13:55,887 --> 00:13:57,944
We know we like what's here.

189
00:13:58,054 --> 00:14:00,418
We know that we want what's here.

190
00:14:00,520 --> 00:14:03,180
But what is here exactly?

191
00:14:03,287 --> 00:14:07,344
Just sit this on your tongue...

192
00:14:09,421 --> 00:14:11,148
for five seconds.

193
00:14:13,688 --> 00:14:16,245
Hmm? Now, chew...

194
00:14:16,354 --> 00:14:17,820
three times.

195
00:14:23,454 --> 00:14:25,477
Manolo, you taste what?

196
00:14:25,587 --> 00:14:27,382
Almond.

197
00:14:27,487 --> 00:14:29,147
Almond?

198
00:14:32,821 --> 00:14:33,809
Cinnamon.

199
00:14:33,921 --> 00:14:34,944
Cinnamon?

200
00:14:35,554 --> 00:14:37,384
Don't scoff.

201
00:14:38,587 --> 00:14:40,383
Yes. Cinnamon.

202
00:14:41,155 --> 00:14:43,553
All right, off you go.

203
00:14:43,655 --> 00:14:45,621
Josemaría, you stay here.

204
00:14:52,055 --> 00:14:56,852
I scolded Manolo for mocking
what he can't experience...

205
00:14:56,956 --> 00:15:00,581
not because he couldn't experience it.

206
00:15:00,689 --> 00:15:03,587
Ah, now, look at this.

207
00:15:03,689 --> 00:15:05,280
Ugly, isn't it?

208
00:15:05,388 --> 00:15:08,377
Just a poor, ordinary little bean.

209
00:15:09,555 --> 00:15:11,487
Yet, patience...

210
00:15:11,588 --> 00:15:15,782
skill, hard work and love...

211
00:15:15,889 --> 00:15:20,288
can unleash the divine flavors
hidden within.

212
00:15:20,389 --> 00:15:21,854
There.

213
00:15:24,289 --> 00:15:26,050
Do you understand the lesson?

214
00:15:28,389 --> 00:15:32,116
But not everyone has a taste
for the divine, you know.

215
00:15:34,090 --> 00:15:36,317
And why is that, I wonder?

216
00:15:39,489 --> 00:15:40,887
Manolo!

217
00:15:40,990 --> 00:15:43,478
Manolo! Wait for me!

218
00:15:43,589 --> 00:15:45,078
Stop! Manolo!

219
00:15:45,190 --> 00:15:47,213
<i>[Manolo Narrating]
My favorite trick in those days...</i>

220
00:15:47,324 --> 00:15:50,449
<i>was stealing Josemaría's dad's chocolates.</i>

221
00:15:50,557 --> 00:15:54,683
<i>But then his dad went bankrupt
and lost the chocolate factory.</i>

222
00:15:54,790 --> 00:15:59,086
<i>And I wasn't allowed to play
with Josemaría anymore.</i>

223
00:15:59,190 --> 00:16:02,054
<i>My dad thought poverty was contagious.</i>

224
00:16:02,157 --> 00:16:04,180
<i>- He said that Josemaría wasn't one of us.
- [Father] One!</i>

225
00:16:04,290 --> 00:16:05,688
- [Groans]
- Two!

226
00:16:05,791 --> 00:16:09,223
<i>- And my dad could be quite persuasive.
- Three!</i>

227
00:16:09,324 --> 00:16:10,415
[Groans]

228
00:16:12,424 --> 00:16:14,322
<i>My dad had more money...</i>

229
00:16:14,424 --> 00:16:18,084
<i>more cars, more houses.</i>

230
00:16:18,191 --> 00:16:21,214
<i>But Josemaría had more dad.</i>

231
00:16:22,224 --> 00:16:25,452
<i>A seed of envy began to grow in me.</i>

232
00:16:25,558 --> 00:16:28,615
<i>In a child's heart, many seeds are planted.</i>

233
00:16:28,724 --> 00:16:30,952
<i>You never quite know what will grow.</i>

234
00:16:36,825 --> 00:16:39,347
Hmm. I'm sure he didn't see us.

235
00:16:46,558 --> 00:16:48,786
[Door Squeaks]

236
00:17:05,459 --> 00:17:07,947
<i>[Wind Howling]</i>

237
00:17:33,659 --> 00:17:37,285
<i>[Manolo Narrating]
Around that time, Josemaría changed.</i>

238
00:17:38,460 --> 00:17:41,620
<i>I'll tell you the story as he told it to me.</i>

239
00:17:44,226 --> 00:17:47,192
<i>One cold winter night...</i>

240
00:17:47,293 --> 00:17:52,157
<i>Josemaría saw footprints
in the snow outside his house.</i>

241
00:17:52,860 --> 00:17:55,257
<i>He followed them.</i>

242
00:17:55,360 --> 00:17:57,758
<i>And then he saw someone.</i>

243
00:18:38,128 --> 00:18:41,356
<i>And he felt that God was calling him.</i>

244
00:18:59,963 --> 00:19:03,087
<i>It wasn't unusual in those days...</i>

245
00:19:03,195 --> 00:19:06,218
<i>for a young man to want to become a priest.</i>

246
00:19:12,996 --> 00:19:16,928
<i>Like it or not, most young men were celibate.</i>

247
00:19:19,696 --> 00:19:21,787
<i>At least as a priest...</i>

248
00:19:21,896 --> 00:19:24,124
<i>you got paid for it.</i>

249
00:19:24,229 --> 00:19:27,218
<i>The priesthood was a career option.</i>

250
00:19:27,330 --> 00:19:32,160
<i>But for Josemaría, it was a sacred calling.</i>

251
00:19:42,697 --> 00:19:46,186
[Church Bells Tolling]

252
00:19:49,264 --> 00:19:53,559
[Women Chattering]

253
00:19:55,531 --> 00:19:57,429
<i>- [Woman #1] You are incorrigible.
- [Woman #2 Chuckles]</i>

254
00:20:01,064 --> 00:20:03,656
Do you know what you're taking on, Son?

255
00:20:03,764 --> 00:20:04,787
Yes, Papa.

256
00:20:04,897 --> 00:20:07,261
No one to love.

257
00:20:07,364 --> 00:20:09,660
Human love, I mean.

258
00:20:09,764 --> 00:20:11,787
No family of your own.

259
00:20:12,831 --> 00:20:14,956
<i>- No sons.
- I know, papi.</i>

260
00:20:17,831 --> 00:20:21,627
And... is this the wisest time
to become a priest?

261
00:20:23,998 --> 00:20:25,623
Probably not.

262
00:20:27,831 --> 00:20:30,991
Is your father still selling
underpants, Josemaría?

263
00:20:31,098 --> 00:20:33,189
[Josemaría]
Backstabber.

264
00:20:33,298 --> 00:20:35,389
Hey, careerist.

265
00:20:35,498 --> 00:20:37,895
- [Man] Fight! Fight!
- [Manolo] You vain little pig!

266
00:20:39,165 --> 00:20:41,960
[Men Chanting]
Fight! Fight!

267
00:20:44,098 --> 00:20:47,622
Fight! Fight! Fight!
Fight! Fight! Fight! Fight! Fight! Fight!

268
00:20:47,732 --> 00:20:49,561
[Whistle Blows]

269
00:20:53,066 --> 00:20:55,361
What lesson do you draw from this?

270
00:20:56,598 --> 00:20:59,621
[Clears Throat]
To control my temper.

271
00:20:59,732 --> 00:21:01,289
Bravo.

272
00:21:03,899 --> 00:21:07,559
Torres, what did you call Seminarian Escrivá?

273
00:21:07,665 --> 00:21:09,222
[Clears Throat]

274
00:21:09,333 --> 00:21:12,197
A vain little... pig.

275
00:21:12,299 --> 00:21:14,197
And you- what did you call Torres?

276
00:21:14,299 --> 00:21:16,356
A backstabbing careerist.

277
00:21:16,466 --> 00:21:18,864
Sorry, Monsignor. I can't stand his type.

278
00:21:18,966 --> 00:21:21,694
A backstabbing careerist.

279
00:21:21,800 --> 00:21:24,095
That sums him up, eh?

280
00:21:24,199 --> 00:21:27,132
What, his father is rich, so he thinks
he can act like a pain in the ass?

281
00:21:27,232 --> 00:21:30,460
That's not the summing up
I had in mind, Escrivá.

282
00:21:31,633 --> 00:21:35,565
Yet, isn't someone else his Father?

283
00:21:36,100 --> 00:21:37,293
And yours?

284
00:21:42,567 --> 00:21:45,226
Remember, the withholding of forgiveness...

285
00:21:45,334 --> 00:21:47,993
is the one thing, as our Lord made clear...

286
00:21:49,000 --> 00:21:52,023
that will not be forgiven.

287
00:21:54,567 --> 00:21:56,055
So...

288
00:21:57,534 --> 00:22:00,261
do you think that two hotheads,
a hypocrite and a loser...

289
00:22:00,367 --> 00:22:02,027
can be good priests?

290
00:22:05,001 --> 00:22:07,126
Well, I think it's possible.

291
00:22:08,801 --> 00:22:10,664
I really do.

292
00:22:12,600 --> 00:22:15,396
<i>[Manolo Narrating]
Well, he was wrong about me.</i>

293
00:22:15,501 --> 00:22:19,194
[Crowd Yelling]

294
00:22:21,301 --> 00:22:23,267
[Shouting, Indistinct]

295
00:22:23,368 --> 00:22:26,061
No, no, no, no! Get away!

296
00:22:26,168 --> 00:22:29,692
- [Whistle Blows]
- Your job is to clear this scum away...

297
00:22:29,802 --> 00:22:31,893
- and let my factory get back to work.
- What can we do?

298
00:22:32,001 --> 00:22:34,058
That's your job! Scum!

299
00:22:37,268 --> 00:22:40,030
- Go!
- But they're just trying
to feed their families, Papa.

300
00:22:40,135 --> 00:22:42,033
- What?
- The workers.

301
00:22:42,135 --> 00:22:43,361
Scum!

302
00:22:43,468 --> 00:22:45,059
Scum!

303
00:22:48,702 --> 00:22:51,827
Manolo, when push comes to shove...

304
00:22:51,935 --> 00:22:54,367
a man has only one duty...

305
00:22:54,469 --> 00:22:56,697
and that is to choose the winning side.

306
00:22:56,802 --> 00:22:58,132
Eh?

307
00:23:01,069 --> 00:23:03,399
- Come on.
- [Whistle Blows]

308
00:23:11,302 --> 00:23:14,359
<i>[Man On P.A. Speaking Spanish]</i>

309
00:23:27,103 --> 00:23:29,035
- Hi.
- Hi.

310
00:23:30,836 --> 00:23:32,768
- Good to see you.
- You too.

311
00:23:32,869 --> 00:23:35,301
- [Horn Honking]
- Nice car.

312
00:23:44,403 --> 00:23:46,369
[Leila]
Where did you get all this?

313
00:23:46,470 --> 00:23:48,459
<i>They're my dad's files from the '50s.</i>

314
00:23:48,570 --> 00:23:50,468
There's more at the hotel.

315
00:23:50,570 --> 00:23:53,968
- He actually sent this stuff to you?
- Yeah.

316
00:23:54,071 --> 00:23:56,628
<i>You are making progress.</i>

317
00:23:56,737 --> 00:23:59,135
What's the reason for the change?

318
00:23:59,237 --> 00:24:02,397
I don't know.
I'm almost scared to find out.

319
00:24:09,471 --> 00:24:11,528
<i>"Foundation for the Sick."</i>

320
00:24:11,638 --> 00:24:13,899
God, such a different world.

321
00:24:16,271 --> 00:24:19,931
<i>[Manolo Narrating] Josemaría wrote to me
once a year until he died.</i>

322
00:24:20,038 --> 00:24:23,697
<i>I never wrote back,
but he kept writing anyway.</i>

323
00:24:23,805 --> 00:24:28,295
<i>In his letters he told me
the turns his life was taking.</i>

324
00:24:29,538 --> 00:24:30,834
Honorio.

325
00:24:30,938 --> 00:24:32,563
[Honorio Gasping]

326
00:24:32,671 --> 00:24:34,160
Josemaría.

327
00:24:35,272 --> 00:24:37,295
Oh, look at you.

328
00:24:37,405 --> 00:24:38,870
Give me your hand.

329
00:24:39,805 --> 00:24:41,862
How's my old employer?

330
00:24:41,972 --> 00:24:44,063
Papa died four years ago, Honorio.

331
00:24:44,172 --> 00:24:45,865
Ah.

332
00:24:45,972 --> 00:24:48,370
I said my first Mass for him.

333
00:24:48,472 --> 00:24:53,495
Do you- you remember...
[Labored Breathing]

334
00:24:53,605 --> 00:24:55,798
The chocolate bean?

335
00:24:55,906 --> 00:24:57,462
Of course.

336
00:24:57,572 --> 00:24:59,538
It was a great lesson.

337
00:24:59,639 --> 00:25:02,935
[Laughing, Coughing]

338
00:25:03,039 --> 00:25:06,630
[Gasping]

339
00:25:08,906 --> 00:25:10,872
I'm sorry. That won't work.

340
00:25:10,973 --> 00:25:12,496
Why not?

341
00:25:14,073 --> 00:25:15,663
Because...

342
00:25:15,772 --> 00:25:17,238
I'm Jewish.

343
00:25:25,440 --> 00:25:27,668
You know, the love of my life is Jewish.

344
00:25:29,974 --> 00:25:33,736
Once I thought of conversion...

345
00:25:35,640 --> 00:25:40,005
but I couldn't dishonor my father.

346
00:25:40,107 --> 00:25:45,335
Honoring our parents is the sweetest precept
of all, Honorio, and very dear to God.

347
00:25:45,441 --> 00:25:48,407
- But Jesus Christ-
- Then he won't turn his back on me...

348
00:25:48,507 --> 00:25:50,632
when I stand before him, will he?

349
00:25:51,541 --> 00:25:53,700
What I know for sure is that...

350
00:25:53,807 --> 00:25:55,706
he loves you very much.

351
00:26:00,607 --> 00:26:02,129
Thank you.

352
00:26:04,674 --> 00:26:07,663
I was afraid of dying here alone.

353
00:26:11,175 --> 00:26:12,970
[Breathing Heavily]

354
00:26:14,774 --> 00:26:18,104
Please pray with me, Father.

355
00:26:18,208 --> 00:26:22,572
- [Saying Prayer In Hebrew]
- And you shall love the Lord your God...

356
00:26:22,674 --> 00:26:24,731
with all your heart...

357
00:26:24,841 --> 00:26:26,739
and with all your mind...

358
00:26:26,841 --> 00:26:28,807
and with all your soul.

359
00:26:29,908 --> 00:26:31,534
Our Father...

360
00:26:31,642 --> 00:26:33,471
who art in heaven...

361
00:26:33,575 --> 00:26:35,541
hallowed be thy name.

362
00:26:35,642 --> 00:26:38,802
Thy kingdom come,
thy will be done on earth...

363
00:26:38,909 --> 00:26:40,875
as it is in heaven.

364
00:26:55,009 --> 00:26:56,975
Good night, Father.

365
00:27:11,409 --> 00:27:14,102
- [Josemaría] Lord, open my eyes.
- [Scribbling]

366
00:27:14,209 --> 00:27:16,698
I am such a blind donkey.

367
00:27:19,476 --> 00:27:22,738
For so long I have felt you
guiding me, but to what?

368
00:27:22,843 --> 00:27:24,866
[Scribbling Continues]

369
00:27:24,977 --> 00:27:27,442
Do you have a purpose
for your donkey, Lord...

370
00:27:27,543 --> 00:27:29,668
but I'm too blind to see it?

371
00:27:35,143 --> 00:27:37,109
You were there tonight, Lord.

372
00:27:37,210 --> 00:27:39,176
I felt you there.

373
00:27:40,210 --> 00:27:42,176
Please be with me now.

374
00:27:44,210 --> 00:27:45,937
Please show me.

375
00:28:15,378 --> 00:28:18,071
<i>[Honorio's Voice]
Ah, now, look at this.</i>

376
00:28:18,178 --> 00:28:21,440
<i>Just a poor, ordinary little bean.</i>

377
00:28:38,778 --> 00:28:40,801
<i>Patience, skill...</i>

378
00:28:40,912 --> 00:28:43,707
<i>hard work and love...</i>

379
00:28:43,812 --> 00:28:48,336
<i>can unleash the divine flavors hidden within.</i>

380
00:29:09,213 --> 00:29:11,179
<i>Do you understand the lesson?</i>

381
00:29:13,280 --> 00:29:15,371
<i>[Chuckling]</i>

382
00:29:16,713 --> 00:29:19,679
[Squeaking]

383
00:29:29,146 --> 00:29:30,612
Yes.

384
00:29:30,714 --> 00:29:32,612
Yes, I see.

385
00:29:32,714 --> 00:29:34,680
Everyone and everything.

386
00:29:34,780 --> 00:29:36,245
Everyone and everything.

387
00:29:41,513 --> 00:29:45,037
Everyone and everything...

388
00:29:45,147 --> 00:29:47,510
for your glory.

389
00:29:50,147 --> 00:29:54,102
Your arms open to all.

390
00:29:55,114 --> 00:29:56,943
One by one.

391
00:30:00,047 --> 00:30:02,741
- Thank you, Lord.
- [Birds Chirping]

392
00:30:03,815 --> 00:30:06,645
So this group of red-blooded
young men are prepared...

393
00:30:06,748 --> 00:30:09,714
to offer themselves completely to God...

394
00:30:09,815 --> 00:30:14,338
in, uh, apostolic work, including celibacy?

395
00:30:14,448 --> 00:30:16,209
Yes, Vicar.

396
00:30:16,314 --> 00:30:18,837
That was the choice I gave them
and one they accepted.

397
00:30:18,948 --> 00:30:20,743
- Really?
- Yes.

398
00:30:20,848 --> 00:30:23,814
[Birds Chirping, Tweeting]

399
00:30:25,514 --> 00:30:26,980
How many?

400
00:30:28,148 --> 00:30:29,478
Uh...

401
00:30:29,582 --> 00:30:30,877
three.

402
00:30:30,982 --> 00:30:32,380
Three.

403
00:30:35,449 --> 00:30:37,210
[Laughs]

404
00:30:38,816 --> 00:30:43,180
<i>[Vicar's Voice] My worry
is that this calling may be delusional.</i>

405
00:30:44,549 --> 00:30:46,913
[Chattering]

406
00:30:54,816 --> 00:30:57,805
<i>[Man]
And this work is to include women?</i>

407
00:30:57,916 --> 00:30:59,677
Yes, Your Excellency.

408
00:30:59,782 --> 00:31:03,112
They will live separately,
but our work will include them...

409
00:31:03,216 --> 00:31:06,410
and will also be open to married people.

410
00:31:06,516 --> 00:31:08,209
[Sighs]

411
00:31:08,316 --> 00:31:10,544
Living in the same institution?

412
00:31:10,650 --> 00:31:12,911
It's not an institution or a movement.

413
00:31:13,016 --> 00:31:15,881
It's just a family of individuals.

414
00:31:15,983 --> 00:31:19,074
And no, married couples will live at home.

415
00:31:20,550 --> 00:31:24,346
[Sighs]
It all seems rather...

416
00:31:25,783 --> 00:31:27,147
Protestant-

417
00:31:28,917 --> 00:31:31,940
that God is to be found in the...

418
00:31:32,050 --> 00:31:34,175
well, vanities of daily life.

419
00:31:34,284 --> 00:31:35,749
Hmm?

420
00:31:35,850 --> 00:31:39,408
Outside holy orders.

421
00:31:40,317 --> 00:31:42,249
No vows. Hmm?

422
00:31:42,351 --> 00:31:44,942
No... habits.

423
00:31:46,584 --> 00:31:50,913
Well, Jesus spent most
of his life working in a shop...

424
00:31:51,017 --> 00:31:52,574
in Nazareth.

425
00:31:54,384 --> 00:31:56,907
God's world is so full of, uh-

426
00:32:03,118 --> 00:32:06,641
[Church Bells Tolling]

427
00:32:08,118 --> 00:32:10,175
[People Chattering In Distance]

428
00:32:12,085 --> 00:32:14,051
God's world is so full of goodness.

429
00:32:15,552 --> 00:32:19,712
If we do them for love,
each daily task can give him glory.

430
00:32:19,818 --> 00:32:24,012
Small but regular acts of love
between husbands and wives...

431
00:32:24,118 --> 00:32:26,744
between friends, between strangers...

432
00:32:26,852 --> 00:32:30,249
each revealing the beauty of his creation.

433
00:32:31,618 --> 00:32:36,550
And you want to open
a new residence in Valencia, huh?

434
00:32:36,652 --> 00:32:39,914
Yes. And one day in New York, Paris...

435
00:32:40,019 --> 00:32:43,076
London and-and... Tokyo.
[Laughs]

436
00:32:43,186 --> 00:32:45,617
It's a long way to Tokyo.

437
00:32:47,252 --> 00:32:49,581
And, uh...

438
00:32:53,186 --> 00:32:55,811
no money yet to speak of.

439
00:32:59,286 --> 00:33:02,047
Well, I can't provide any.

440
00:33:02,152 --> 00:33:04,675
No, I didn't come to ask for that.

441
00:33:04,786 --> 00:33:08,946
I ask merely for your permission-
for me and for the work.

442
00:33:13,953 --> 00:33:15,942
And you shall have them.

443
00:33:16,786 --> 00:33:20,082
Father Escrivá...

444
00:33:20,187 --> 00:33:24,142
I offer you a job as my secretary.

445
00:33:24,253 --> 00:33:26,242
In time this will lead to a career...

446
00:33:26,354 --> 00:33:29,445
that might grant you the influence
that you would need...

447
00:33:29,554 --> 00:33:33,077
to realize this- this dream of yours.

448
00:33:33,187 --> 00:33:35,779
So, what do you say?

449
00:33:37,020 --> 00:33:38,384
I said no, thank you.

450
00:33:38,487 --> 00:33:39,544
Santi.

451
00:33:41,320 --> 00:33:43,218
Now, it won't be easy, I know.

452
00:33:43,320 --> 00:33:47,083
But I'll always see that there's a roof
over your heads and food on the table.

453
00:33:47,188 --> 00:33:49,017
No? Huh?

454
00:33:49,121 --> 00:33:51,314
- Josemaría-
- Actually...

455
00:33:51,420 --> 00:33:53,182
I have an idea.

456
00:33:53,288 --> 00:33:59,551
<i>[Children]
Pecunia in arboribus non crescit.</i>

457
00:33:59,654 --> 00:34:02,553
<i>Crescit. Good. Okay. Agustin.</i>

458
00:34:02,654 --> 00:34:05,086
<i>Pec- Pec-</i>

459
00:34:05,188 --> 00:34:07,086
<i>- Pecunia.
- I can't do it, sir.</i>

460
00:34:07,188 --> 00:34:09,746
- [Other Children Laugh]
- Yes, you can. Shh, shh. Yes, you can.

461
00:34:09,854 --> 00:34:11,911
You will learn, and I will learn to teach it.

462
00:34:12,021 --> 00:34:14,419
[Coughing]

463
00:34:14,521 --> 00:34:15,987
Oh, no. Damn it!

464
00:34:16,088 --> 00:34:17,554
Stay here.

465
00:34:21,188 --> 00:34:23,018
- [Water Running]
- [Man Coughs]

466
00:34:23,122 --> 00:34:25,281
[Groans]
I'm sorry, Father.

467
00:34:25,388 --> 00:34:28,014
Sorry. But I can't-

468
00:34:28,122 --> 00:34:30,644
The smell. I can't.

469
00:34:30,755 --> 00:34:33,381
- [Laughing]
- [Coughing]

470
00:34:33,489 --> 00:34:35,580
[Coughing Continues]

471
00:34:35,688 --> 00:34:37,154
How's your Latin?

472
00:34:38,422 --> 00:34:39,717
Go.

473
00:34:39,822 --> 00:34:41,288
[Man] No.

474
00:34:43,888 --> 00:34:45,320
Go on. Go.

475
00:34:45,422 --> 00:34:47,684
- Go, go, go. Go.
- [Laughing]

476
00:34:50,122 --> 00:34:52,350
- [Dog Barking]
- [Crowd Chattering]

477
00:34:52,456 --> 00:34:55,581
- [Horn Honking]
- [Manolo] Union scum.

478
00:34:55,689 --> 00:34:57,178
Drive through them!

479
00:34:58,090 --> 00:34:59,646
Don't. Thugs.

480
00:34:59,756 --> 00:35:01,949
How can you do this?
You know my father's ill.

481
00:35:02,056 --> 00:35:03,851
Then God is just.

482
00:35:03,956 --> 00:35:07,480
- [Yelling]
- [Whistle Blows]

483
00:35:12,623 --> 00:35:16,111
Damn unions.
I've always said they're going to kill him.

484
00:35:16,223 --> 00:35:19,383
[Woman]
It's a stroke. The doctor just left.

485
00:35:19,490 --> 00:35:22,217
[Manolo]
No. No.

486
00:35:27,156 --> 00:35:28,247
Papa.

487
00:35:29,857 --> 00:35:32,482
[Wheezing]

488
00:35:32,590 --> 00:35:34,647
Papa.

489
00:35:34,757 --> 00:35:36,280
[Nurse]
He can't speak.

490
00:35:36,390 --> 00:35:39,982
What? What did the doctor say?

491
00:35:40,091 --> 00:35:42,522
That it's God's will.

492
00:35:42,623 --> 00:35:44,055
Get out of here.

493
00:35:44,157 --> 00:35:45,918
Manolo, please.

494
00:35:46,024 --> 00:35:47,490
Get out of here.

495
00:35:48,324 --> 00:35:49,789
Get out!

496
00:35:49,890 --> 00:35:51,356
Get out!

497
00:36:01,124 --> 00:36:04,181
[Wheezing]

498
00:36:04,291 --> 00:36:05,814
Papa.

499
00:36:08,192 --> 00:36:09,953
Papa?

500
00:36:14,791 --> 00:36:16,280
Papa.

501
00:36:19,591 --> 00:36:23,388
## [Piano]

502
00:36:41,093 --> 00:36:42,558
Thank you.

503
00:36:57,426 --> 00:36:59,324
Good afternoon, brother.

504
00:37:00,493 --> 00:37:01,481
Brother?

505
00:37:01,593 --> 00:37:03,422
Uh, Josemaría.

506
00:37:04,693 --> 00:37:07,284
I know who you are, Josemaría.

507
00:37:12,027 --> 00:37:14,288
[Clears Throat]

508
00:37:14,393 --> 00:37:17,359
I heard your sad news, Manolo.

509
00:37:17,460 --> 00:37:19,483
You have been in my prayers.

510
00:37:19,593 --> 00:37:23,616
Thank you.
But I don't need your brand of sympathy-

511
00:37:23,727 --> 00:37:25,216
however sincere.

512
00:37:25,327 --> 00:37:28,020
Manolo,
whatever struggles you are experiencing-

513
00:37:28,127 --> 00:37:31,820
- Struggles?
- Well, whatever doubts you may be having.

514
00:37:31,927 --> 00:37:34,893
Doubts. Struggles.

515
00:37:34,994 --> 00:37:39,552
Josemaría, I blundered into the seminary
in deference to my mother.

516
00:37:39,661 --> 00:37:42,388
I left because I wasn't priest material.

517
00:37:43,427 --> 00:37:45,689
As you know.

518
00:37:45,794 --> 00:37:49,726
Well, maybe not, but it doesn't mean
you're not saint material.

519
00:37:50,461 --> 00:37:51,825
[Chuckles]

520
00:37:54,095 --> 00:37:56,254
You know...

521
00:37:56,361 --> 00:38:00,760
my recurring nightmare
is that I was partly to blame for you leaving.

522
00:38:00,861 --> 00:38:03,020
No, Josemaría.

523
00:38:03,128 --> 00:38:05,923
Unlike you,
I chose to live in the real world.

524
00:38:06,028 --> 00:38:08,755
But I appreciate your concern.

525
00:38:08,861 --> 00:38:10,225
It's not concern, Manolo.

526
00:38:13,428 --> 00:38:14,859
It's love.

527
00:38:14,961 --> 00:38:18,359
Our Lord said love,
and love is what he meant.

528
00:38:18,462 --> 00:38:21,155
And it's what we owe each other. No?

529
00:38:22,929 --> 00:38:25,292
Josemaría, the truth is...

530
00:38:25,395 --> 00:38:28,123
we are born alone and we die alone.

531
00:38:28,228 --> 00:38:31,388
All we have in between
is a battle I intend to win.

532
00:38:31,495 --> 00:38:34,155
The rest is, frankly, sentimental drivel.

533
00:38:35,428 --> 00:38:38,553
- ## [Resumes]
- Well, I will leave you.

534
00:38:39,996 --> 00:38:41,360
Call on me.

535
00:38:42,929 --> 00:38:44,395
I'll come, I promise.

536
00:38:47,529 --> 00:38:50,495
Josemaría. You don't give up, do you?

537
00:38:50,596 --> 00:38:53,585
It may help you to find some meaning
for your suffering, Manolo.

538
00:38:53,696 --> 00:38:57,253
Suffering has no meaning. It's meaningless.

539
00:38:57,363 --> 00:38:59,625
If you can show me otherwise,
I'll kiss your ass.

540
00:38:59,730 --> 00:39:01,195
<i>That's my promise.</i>

541
00:39:02,329 --> 00:39:04,795
I know what it is to be angry at life.

542
00:39:07,197 --> 00:39:09,424
Please be careful
where that leads you, Manolo.

543
00:39:11,596 --> 00:39:12,358
Sheep.

544
00:39:38,931 --> 00:39:42,920
<i>[Manolo Narrating] Around the time
that Josemaría got a call from God...</i>

545
00:39:43,031 --> 00:39:45,293
<i>I also got a call-</i>

546
00:39:45,398 --> 00:39:48,727
<i>from an old friend of my father's.</i>

547
00:39:48,831 --> 00:39:50,763
Ah, Torres.

548
00:39:50,864 --> 00:39:53,659
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

549
00:39:53,764 --> 00:39:56,730
## [Soldiers Singing In Spanish]

550
00:40:02,264 --> 00:40:04,492
- Well?
- A spy?

551
00:40:04,598 --> 00:40:06,325
Yes. You.

552
00:40:06,431 --> 00:40:08,158
But I expected something more.

553
00:40:08,264 --> 00:40:11,822
With the king gone,
Spain has lost its center of gravity.

554
00:40:11,932 --> 00:40:15,228
Which we will now re-create,
by force if needs be.

555
00:40:15,331 --> 00:40:17,093
<i>[Man #2]
And other means.</i>

556
00:40:17,199 --> 00:40:19,562
But our government's elected. It's popular.

557
00:40:19,665 --> 00:40:20,858
Its time is over.

558
00:40:20,965 --> 00:40:22,590
<i>[Man #1]
The government is a rotten biscuit.</i>

559
00:40:22,698 --> 00:40:25,562
- Tap it and see the maggots emerge.
- Maggots?

560
00:40:25,665 --> 00:40:27,688
Socialists who want a socialist state.

561
00:40:27,798 --> 00:40:29,696
Stalinists who want a Stalinist state.

562
00:40:29,798 --> 00:40:31,662
Anarchists who want no state at all.

563
00:40:31,765 --> 00:40:34,698
Manolo, we want to create a new Spain.

564
00:40:34,799 --> 00:40:37,458
<i>- [Man #1] A united Spain.
- Cleansed with blood if necessary.</i>

565
00:40:37,566 --> 00:40:40,361
<i>[Man #1]
Resurrected, great and as it once was-</i>

566
00:40:40,466 --> 00:40:42,227
<i>- ordered, vigorous.
- [Man #2] And admired.</i>

567
00:40:42,332 --> 00:40:45,094
- [Pounding On Table]
- [Speaking German]

568
00:40:48,866 --> 00:40:52,094
## [Singing In Spanish]

569
00:40:56,733 --> 00:40:59,165
<i>[Manolo Narrating]
They called us fascists.</i>

570
00:40:59,266 --> 00:41:01,993
<i>- We called them communists.
- ## [March]</i>

571
00:41:02,100 --> 00:41:06,032
<i>Really, the world was much
more complicated than that.</i>

572
00:41:06,133 --> 00:41:09,099
<i>But many preferred to see it
in those simple terms.</i>

573
00:41:09,200 --> 00:41:13,496
<i>Three years later,
half a million people were dead-</i>

574
00:41:13,600 --> 00:41:16,157
<i>most of them civilians.</i>

575
00:41:16,266 --> 00:41:18,596
<i>But even in times like these...</i>

576
00:41:18,700 --> 00:41:23,564
<i>some people are more interested
in hats and shoes.</i>

577
00:41:29,201 --> 00:41:31,758
[Mother]
I thought you were going to buy new shoes.

578
00:41:31,867 --> 00:41:36,822
Uh, yes, I was, but, uh,
something else came up.

579
00:41:36,934 --> 00:41:41,594
- What was that?
- No. L- I met an old lady who-

580
00:41:41,701 --> 00:41:43,564
<i>- Who needed a hat.
- [Man #2] And some breakfast?</i>

581
00:41:43,668 --> 00:41:45,826
<i>- [Man #1] Yes, and some lunch.
- Thank you.</i>

582
00:41:45,934 --> 00:41:47,264
[Chuckling]

583
00:41:47,368 --> 00:41:50,334
Sit down, please, Pedro, Isidoro.

584
00:41:50,434 --> 00:41:51,957
Well, uh-

585
00:41:54,002 --> 00:41:55,695
- So?
- [Clears Throat]

586
00:41:55,801 --> 00:41:59,426
This group that keeps you from your homes-
what is it called?

587
00:41:59,534 --> 00:42:01,363
We don't have a name, Mama.

588
00:42:01,468 --> 00:42:03,196
We just refer to it as God's work.

589
00:42:04,202 --> 00:42:05,895
Latin would sound better.

590
00:42:06,968 --> 00:42:10,059
<i>Uh, Opus Dei.</i>

591
00:42:14,035 --> 00:42:16,501
<i>##[Radio... Guitar]</i>

592
00:42:18,135 --> 00:42:20,158
<i>[Volume Increases]</i>

593
00:42:20,268 --> 00:42:23,234
<i>##[Folk Chorus Singing In Spanish]</i>

594
00:42:28,936 --> 00:42:31,697
Well, your donkey may lack funds...

595
00:42:31,802 --> 00:42:33,768
but the work has found its name.

596
00:42:36,535 --> 00:42:37,933
[Chuckling]
What's next?

597
00:42:45,003 --> 00:42:47,935
<i>##[Chorus Singing In Spanish]</i>

598
00:42:56,969 --> 00:42:58,799
[Chattering, Cheering]

599
00:42:58,903 --> 00:43:00,391
<i>Vamos.</i>

600
00:43:04,303 --> 00:43:05,769
<i>Está bien.</i>

601
00:43:07,536 --> 00:43:12,196
<i>[Manolo Narrating]
A communist strike killed my father.</i>

602
00:43:12,303 --> 00:43:15,168
<i>Now it was my turn to strike.</i>

603
00:43:15,270 --> 00:43:17,361
<i>##[Continues]</i>

604
00:43:25,637 --> 00:43:27,694
- [Man Grunting]
- Get out of the car!

605
00:43:27,803 --> 00:43:30,201
- Come here, scum!
- [Man Shouts]

606
00:43:31,137 --> 00:43:33,535
- Put the hood on him!
- Please! No!

607
00:43:33,637 --> 00:43:35,102
[Muffled Shouting]

608
00:43:35,204 --> 00:43:38,170
Yeah, we'll show you how just God is.

609
00:43:38,270 --> 00:43:40,566
- In the boss's car.
- [Muffled Screaming]

610
00:43:42,038 --> 00:43:43,867
Let's go!

611
00:44:00,671 --> 00:44:03,001
[Car Doors Open, Close]

612
00:44:13,171 --> 00:44:16,365
[Whimpering]

613
00:44:17,972 --> 00:44:20,063
Where's your gun?

614
00:44:20,172 --> 00:44:22,070
This is not a game.

615
00:44:22,172 --> 00:44:24,899
He killed your father.

616
00:44:26,139 --> 00:44:28,502
Ah, damn it.
The bastard's shitting his pants.

617
00:44:28,605 --> 00:44:30,696
- [Whimpering]
- Do it.

618
00:44:30,805 --> 00:44:33,397
[Muffled Screaming]

619
00:44:33,506 --> 00:44:35,563
Do it, damn it.

620
00:44:47,906 --> 00:44:49,371
[Engine Starts]

621
00:44:59,339 --> 00:45:00,999
Pedro.

622
00:45:01,107 --> 00:45:03,300
- [Laughs] You're crazy.
- No, I'm not.

623
00:45:03,407 --> 00:45:05,202
You're crazy.

624
00:45:05,307 --> 00:45:07,000
He'll hate the whole idea.

625
00:45:07,107 --> 00:45:09,005
Well, let's ask him.

626
00:45:09,107 --> 00:45:10,505
Ask me?

627
00:45:10,607 --> 00:45:12,868
This. We're gonna put them up
all over Madrid.

628
00:45:12,973 --> 00:45:14,496
Look.

629
00:45:15,940 --> 00:45:17,167
[Pedro]
Not me, Father. Not me.

630
00:45:17,273 --> 00:45:20,000
- A crusade?
- Yes, Father.

631
00:45:20,107 --> 00:45:24,062
Using the cross to incite hatred and anger-
that's Christian?

632
00:45:24,173 --> 00:45:25,696
Well, maybe not.

633
00:45:25,807 --> 00:45:28,500
But, Father, the government
is openly attacking the church.

634
00:45:28,607 --> 00:45:30,539
No, it isn't.
It's trying to modernize Spain.

635
00:45:30,640 --> 00:45:32,106
Come on, Pedro.

636
00:45:32,208 --> 00:45:34,071
If we don't do something,
we are just cowards.

637
00:45:34,174 --> 00:45:35,605
- Or worse- traitors.
- Traitors.

638
00:45:35,707 --> 00:45:37,502
- Traitors?
- Yes, Paco. Traitors.

639
00:45:37,607 --> 00:45:39,039
That's what people are saying.

640
00:45:39,141 --> 00:45:41,437
Standing by while the church gets attacked-

641
00:45:41,540 --> 00:45:43,564
how is that being a good Catholic?

642
00:45:43,674 --> 00:45:46,607
Pedro, is it understandable
to want to protect the church?

643
00:45:46,707 --> 00:45:47,832
Yes, Father, but-

644
00:45:47,941 --> 00:45:50,669
Juan, is it understandable
to want social justice?

645
00:45:50,775 --> 00:45:51,933
Yes, of course.

646
00:45:52,041 --> 00:45:54,599
Good. So the question is,
how do we achieve both?

647
00:45:54,708 --> 00:45:56,003
[Mother]
By feeding the hungry.

648
00:45:56,108 --> 00:45:59,233
And lunch is ready, so sit down now.

649
00:46:03,708 --> 00:46:06,038
So we just let the matter drop?

650
00:46:06,142 --> 00:46:07,630
No.

651
00:46:07,742 --> 00:46:10,401
Look, I'm not going
to tell you what to think.

652
00:46:10,508 --> 00:46:13,599
God gave each of you a brain
and reason and a conscience.

653
00:46:13,708 --> 00:46:16,606
Why? So that you can
come to conclusions on your own...

654
00:46:16,708 --> 00:46:19,106
and take personal responsibility for them.

655
00:46:19,209 --> 00:46:23,733
But before rushing to act-

656
00:46:23,842 --> 00:46:26,536
before trying to change the world-

657
00:46:26,642 --> 00:46:29,005
first think about changing yourselves.

658
00:46:30,709 --> 00:46:34,232
We're building something vital here together.

659
00:46:34,342 --> 00:46:36,331
Now- especially now-

660
00:46:36,442 --> 00:46:39,704
we have to be sowers of peace and joy.

661
00:46:42,476 --> 00:46:44,374
And lunch, Mama.

662
00:46:47,709 --> 00:46:50,437
- Father!
- [Loud Clatter]

663
00:46:50,542 --> 00:46:52,236
They've started killing priests.

664
00:46:52,343 --> 00:46:55,571
- What?
- It's in the newspaper.

665
00:46:55,676 --> 00:46:57,040
[Paco]
Oh, my God.

666
00:46:57,143 --> 00:46:59,336
- Where?
- Here in Madrid.

667
00:46:59,443 --> 00:47:01,500
Let me see.

668
00:47:03,943 --> 00:47:06,432
So, what do we do now, Father?

669
00:47:06,543 --> 00:47:08,668
Exactly what I just said, Juan.

670
00:47:10,377 --> 00:47:11,900
Please.

671
00:47:14,977 --> 00:47:17,807
Bless us, O Lord, and these thy gifts...

672
00:47:17,910 --> 00:47:19,341
which we are about to receive...

673
00:47:19,443 --> 00:47:22,069
from your bounty, through Christ our Lord.

674
00:47:22,177 --> 00:47:24,200
- Amen.
- [Others] Amen.

675
00:47:29,844 --> 00:47:31,776
[Crowd Shouting]

676
00:47:46,644 --> 00:47:48,701
[Shouting, Cheering]

677
00:47:55,811 --> 00:47:58,334
[Bell Clanging]

678
00:48:00,711 --> 00:48:02,234
[Man]
Oh, what have we here?

679
00:48:02,345 --> 00:48:03,368
Found a cockroach.

680
00:48:03,479 --> 00:48:04,637
Hey, watch where you're going.

681
00:48:04,745 --> 00:48:06,211
How about we squash it, eh?

682
00:48:06,312 --> 00:48:08,107
- [Muttering]
- Let's squash him.

683
00:48:10,412 --> 00:48:12,605
[Man]
Well, well, well.

684
00:48:12,712 --> 00:48:14,769
- Priest.
- What have we got here?

685
00:48:16,412 --> 00:48:17,878
- A little priest?
- Oh, yeah.

686
00:48:17,979 --> 00:48:19,569
- Whoa!
- Look there.

687
00:48:19,679 --> 00:48:21,144
- I'm sorry.
- What's he carrying?

688
00:48:21,245 --> 00:48:23,677
So, what have we got there? Huh?

689
00:48:23,779 --> 00:48:26,438
- Come on. Show us.
- No, no. Please. Please.

690
00:48:26,545 --> 00:48:29,875
Give me the packet,
or I stick you with this.

691
00:48:29,979 --> 00:48:31,467
[Woman]
Stab the parasite.

692
00:48:31,579 --> 00:48:33,772
I'm not a parasite.

693
00:48:33,879 --> 00:48:35,708
I have to work for a living,
just like all of you.

694
00:48:35,812 --> 00:48:38,176
Work for a living?
You know what working for a living is?

695
00:48:38,779 --> 00:48:40,268
That's enough!

696
00:48:40,380 --> 00:48:43,540
- That's enough!
- [Shouting, Muttering]

697
00:48:43,646 --> 00:48:46,805
Please! Get on the next one.

698
00:48:46,912 --> 00:48:48,708
- Relax.
- [All Muttering]

699
00:48:48,813 --> 00:48:50,210
- Relax, old man.
- Please.

700
00:48:50,313 --> 00:48:51,643
See you later, priest.

701
00:48:51,747 --> 00:48:53,713
- I'm on your side.
- Fascist.

702
00:48:53,813 --> 00:48:56,176
- [Muttering, Laughing]
- Come on.

703
00:48:56,279 --> 00:48:58,268
- We'll get you next time.
- Yeah.

704
00:49:04,180 --> 00:49:06,907
[Whistle Blows]

705
00:49:11,381 --> 00:49:16,109
They've got a thing
against enemies of their class.

706
00:49:16,214 --> 00:49:18,578
- Can't say I blame them.
- No. I know.

707
00:49:18,681 --> 00:49:22,010
All part of creating
this new, more civilized Spain.

708
00:49:22,114 --> 00:49:23,512
Exactly.

709
00:49:23,614 --> 00:49:26,011
And how will uncivilized behavior
accomplish that?

710
00:49:26,114 --> 00:49:28,376
Can't make an omelet without breaking eggs.

711
00:49:28,481 --> 00:49:30,310
No. Life is not an omelet.

712
00:49:30,414 --> 00:49:32,209
And people are not eggs.

713
00:49:32,314 --> 00:49:36,406
Okay. Hey, if I was you...

714
00:49:36,514 --> 00:49:39,947
I'd stop wandering about
in that costume of yours.

715
00:49:40,048 --> 00:49:41,877
It won't protect you anymore.

716
00:49:41,981 --> 00:49:44,345
I don't wear this for protection.

717
00:49:44,447 --> 00:49:47,505
You got balls for a bourgeois ass.

718
00:49:51,648 --> 00:49:54,045
[Boy]
One, two. One, two.

719
00:49:54,148 --> 00:49:56,273
One, two. One, two.

720
00:49:56,382 --> 00:49:58,780
One, two. One, two.

721
00:49:58,881 --> 00:50:01,507
One, two. One, two.

722
00:50:01,615 --> 00:50:02,706
Thank you, Father.

723
00:50:02,815 --> 00:50:04,280
One, two. Halt.

724
00:50:04,382 --> 00:50:06,814
[Cheering, Singing]

725
00:50:06,915 --> 00:50:09,006
<i>[Manolo Narrating]
From their palaces, the bishops said...</i>

726
00:50:09,116 --> 00:50:11,809
<i>"The meek shall inherit the earth."</i>

727
00:50:13,482 --> 00:50:14,709
Ready!

728
00:50:15,648 --> 00:50:17,205
Aim! Fire!

729
00:50:17,316 --> 00:50:18,611
- [Lmitating Gunshots]
- [Groans]

730
00:50:18,715 --> 00:50:21,909
- [Man] Hey!
- [Children Laughing]

731
00:50:24,648 --> 00:50:26,910
<i>But the meek were tired of waiting.</i>

732
00:50:27,016 --> 00:50:28,380
- [Groans]
- [Children Laughing]

733
00:50:30,782 --> 00:50:33,715
<i>They took the bishops and their palaces.</i>

734
00:50:34,850 --> 00:50:37,008
<i>He was lucky it was only a rock.</i>

735
00:50:43,282 --> 00:50:44,578
Hello?

736
00:50:47,950 --> 00:50:49,246
Juan? Paco?

737
00:50:54,183 --> 00:50:56,206
Happy birthday!

738
00:50:56,317 --> 00:50:58,545
[All Exclaiming, Laughing]

739
00:50:59,983 --> 00:51:01,506
It's not my birthday.

740
00:51:01,617 --> 00:51:04,344
Please. Come on.

741
00:51:04,450 --> 00:51:05,575
Josemaría...

742
00:51:05,684 --> 00:51:07,309
as your brother, I have been chosen...

743
00:51:07,417 --> 00:51:10,940
to ask you to celebrate
our second year together...

744
00:51:11,050 --> 00:51:12,516
by removing your shoes.

745
00:51:12,617 --> 00:51:14,048
- [All Laughing]
- Yes, Father!

746
00:51:14,150 --> 00:51:16,116
- Take them off.
- Take off your shoes.

747
00:51:16,217 --> 00:51:19,082
- Shoes off. Come on, Father.
- No.

748
00:51:19,183 --> 00:51:20,774
- Yes.
- Yes.

749
00:51:20,884 --> 00:51:22,975
- The shoes.
- Take them off.

750
00:51:24,218 --> 00:51:26,207
[All Chuckling]

751
00:51:27,284 --> 00:51:30,943
- Behold a simple shoe.
- [All Murmur]

752
00:51:31,051 --> 00:51:32,607
But is it what it seems?

753
00:51:32,717 --> 00:51:33,705
- Yes.
- Yes.

754
00:51:33,817 --> 00:51:38,614
No. It is, in fact, a hole.

755
00:51:38,717 --> 00:51:40,047
[All Laughing]

756
00:51:40,151 --> 00:51:41,844
A hole masquerading as a shoe.

757
00:51:41,951 --> 00:51:43,383
Oh!

758
00:51:43,485 --> 00:51:46,178
And a hole surrounded by leather.

759
00:51:47,518 --> 00:51:48,916
[Laughing Continues]

760
00:51:49,018 --> 00:51:50,678
Shh! Shh!

761
00:51:50,785 --> 00:51:55,342
<i>But also a testament
to 20 kilometers a day...</i>

762
00:51:55,451 --> 00:51:57,213
seven days a week...

763
00:51:57,318 --> 00:51:59,750
rain and shine.

764
00:52:00,952 --> 00:52:02,383
- Yes!
- Thank you.

765
00:52:02,485 --> 00:52:06,316
And in pity for this innocent shoe...

766
00:52:06,419 --> 00:52:09,510
we have also pooled together for-

767
00:52:09,618 --> 00:52:11,050
- Ta-da!
- [All Cheering]

768
00:52:11,152 --> 00:52:14,175
- [Man] What nice shoes.
- Try them on.

769
00:52:14,285 --> 00:52:17,251
- [Gunshot]
- [Pedro] Get down! Get down!

770
00:52:18,252 --> 00:52:19,718
[Mother]
Santiago, get down!

771
00:52:19,819 --> 00:52:20,909
- Santi!
- God!

772
00:52:21,019 --> 00:52:24,008
[Gunshots]

773
00:52:24,119 --> 00:52:26,085
Get down!

774
00:52:26,185 --> 00:52:28,777
[Gunshots Continue Outside]

775
00:52:28,886 --> 00:52:31,114
<i>[Male Announcer]
This is an announcement
from your government.</i>

776
00:52:31,219 --> 00:52:33,412
<i>There has been a military uprising.</i>

777
00:52:33,519 --> 00:52:37,383
<i>The army has recruited
the Spanish colonial army of Morocco.</i>

778
00:52:37,486 --> 00:52:40,248
<i>All able-bodied Spaniards
who love their country-</i>

779
00:52:40,486 --> 00:52:43,543
[Clock Ticking]

780
00:52:50,720 --> 00:52:54,083
<i>[Manolo Narrating]
It's remarkably easy to join a war.</i>

781
00:52:54,186 --> 00:52:56,084
[Shouting, Cheering]

782
00:52:56,186 --> 00:52:58,846
<i>I wormed my way into a communist brigade.</i>

783
00:52:58,954 --> 00:53:04,818
<i>- ## [Singing In Spanish]
- So far, I was enjoying being a spy.</i>

784
00:53:04,920 --> 00:53:08,182
<i>There's something inspiring
about the common purpose...</i>

785
00:53:08,286 --> 00:53:10,775
<i>even when it's not yours.</i>

786
00:53:10,887 --> 00:53:14,444
<i>I can't describe that ecstasy
of belonging to a crowd-</i>

787
00:53:14,553 --> 00:53:16,985
<i>even when it's the enemy.</i>

788
00:53:17,087 --> 00:53:19,553
<i>There's no better feeling.</i>

789
00:53:19,653 --> 00:53:22,518
<i>Well, apart from one.</i>

790
00:53:36,821 --> 00:53:38,616
Cat got your tongue, comrade?

791
00:53:43,188 --> 00:53:46,245
## [Singing Continues]

792
00:53:55,389 --> 00:53:58,253
[Crowd Applauding, Cheering]

793
00:54:03,789 --> 00:54:06,186
[Microphone Feedback]

794
00:54:07,288 --> 00:54:09,584
[Man]
So many young people-

795
00:54:09,689 --> 00:54:12,382
what do you know of suffering and death?

796
00:54:12,489 --> 00:54:14,978
<i>How they will taunt you- "Is it worth it?"</i>

797
00:54:15,089 --> 00:54:17,748
<i>They will ask again and again,
"Is it worth it?"</i>

798
00:54:19,322 --> 00:54:23,550
<i>And what will fill your hearts
with the answer "Yes"? Yes!</i>

799
00:54:24,822 --> 00:54:27,686
- Hatred of oppression? Of tyranny?
- [Crowd] Yes!

800
00:54:27,789 --> 00:54:30,687
- Hatred of those who treat us like animals-
- [Crowd Cheering]

801
00:54:30,789 --> 00:54:33,812
Denying our hopes and stifling our lives?

802
00:54:33,922 --> 00:54:35,013
Yes!

803
00:54:35,123 --> 00:54:37,112
But more.

804
00:54:39,523 --> 00:54:42,250
It will be faith-

805
00:54:42,356 --> 00:54:47,118
faith that a new world will be
born from the blood of the old.

806
00:54:47,223 --> 00:54:48,519
[Cheering]

807
00:54:48,623 --> 00:54:51,453
And comradeship, my brothers and sisters.

808
00:54:52,757 --> 00:54:54,814
And courage-

809
00:54:54,923 --> 00:54:56,946
courage to burst from our cages...

810
00:54:57,057 --> 00:54:59,579
and set ourselves free to live noble...

811
00:54:59,690 --> 00:55:01,952
as the eagle hovering
above his mountain peak.

812
00:55:03,290 --> 00:55:06,586
- Or die in the attempt!
- [Cheering]

813
00:55:09,723 --> 00:55:12,189
<i>##[Orchestra On P.A.]</i>

814
00:55:13,857 --> 00:55:18,722
<i>- ##[Chorus Singing..."The Internationale"]
- Thanks.</i>

815
00:55:20,924 --> 00:55:23,219
- Name and country.
- Régis. France.

816
00:55:23,324 --> 00:55:25,552
- Name and country.
- Jan. South Africa.

817
00:55:25,657 --> 00:55:29,055
- Name and country.
- Petofi, lldiko. Hungary, sir.

818
00:55:29,158 --> 00:55:32,249
<i>There are no "sirs" in the Iron Brigade,
lldiko.</i>

819
00:55:32,357 --> 00:55:34,381
Peasants, factory workers...

820
00:55:34,491 --> 00:55:36,458
some like me- escaped convicts.

821
00:55:36,557 --> 00:55:39,251
We are what we are, but we are all equal.

822
00:55:39,358 --> 00:55:41,085
But still fighting to be free-

823
00:55:41,191 --> 00:55:42,487
as we all wish to be!

824
00:55:42,592 --> 00:55:44,581
[Cheering]

825
00:55:45,392 --> 00:55:46,857
Lldiko Petofi.

826
00:55:46,958 --> 00:55:48,254
Yes, sir.

827
00:55:49,858 --> 00:55:52,450
- Oriol.
- Yes, Oriol.

828
00:55:57,291 --> 00:55:58,587
<i>"Yes, Oriol."</i>

829
00:56:02,258 --> 00:56:04,747
- Jealous?
- No.

830
00:56:05,458 --> 00:56:07,390
What is your name?

831
00:56:08,658 --> 00:56:09,954
Manolo.

832
00:56:12,459 --> 00:56:13,947
<i>[Man On P.A.]
Viva la República!</i>

833
00:56:14,059 --> 00:56:16,423
<i>[All]
Vival [Cheering]</i>

834
00:56:19,859 --> 00:56:22,916
[Man Groaning]

835
00:56:23,026 --> 00:56:24,014
[Whistle Blows]

836
00:56:24,126 --> 00:56:25,422
Go, go, go!

837
00:56:32,760 --> 00:56:34,316
[Man Shouts]

838
00:56:40,726 --> 00:56:42,419
Let's go, let's go, let's go!

839
00:56:42,960 --> 00:56:44,550
Come on!

840
00:56:44,659 --> 00:56:46,125
Come on!

841
00:56:49,893 --> 00:56:51,553
Come on!

842
00:56:52,993 --> 00:56:54,516
Come on!

843
00:56:55,327 --> 00:56:56,452
Come on!

844
00:56:59,394 --> 00:57:01,360
[Man Shouts]

845
00:57:08,961 --> 00:57:11,688
Take cover! Move!

846
00:57:11,794 --> 00:57:15,090
[All Shouting]

847
00:57:18,727 --> 00:57:20,625
Fire! Fire! Fire!

848
00:57:27,961 --> 00:57:29,824
[Groans]

849
00:57:35,294 --> 00:57:37,886
Lldi- Ildi- Ildiko!

850
00:57:37,994 --> 00:57:40,085
[Whimpering]

851
00:57:40,194 --> 00:57:43,217
Stop. Go back. Face them.

852
00:57:43,328 --> 00:57:45,260
Thank the bastards for testing your bravery.

853
00:57:51,862 --> 00:57:53,226
Go!

854
00:57:54,062 --> 00:57:56,392
Go! Go. Go.

855
00:57:57,029 --> 00:57:58,551
- Torres.
- Yeah.

856
00:57:58,661 --> 00:58:00,287
Look after her.

857
00:58:03,529 --> 00:58:05,688
[Man]
Forward!

858
00:58:11,029 --> 00:58:13,086
Oh, God. I'm such a coward.

859
00:58:13,195 --> 00:58:14,889
Me too.

860
00:58:32,829 --> 00:58:34,590
I don't feel right about this.

861
00:58:34,696 --> 00:58:36,162
You read the newspapers.

862
00:58:36,263 --> 00:58:39,320
They don't exactly like priests out there,
Father.

863
00:58:39,430 --> 00:58:41,726
Then don't call me Father
when I am dressed like this.

864
00:58:43,330 --> 00:58:45,228
Call me Mariano.

865
00:58:45,330 --> 00:58:47,728
- [Doorbell Buzzing]
- That's Vargas.

866
00:58:47,830 --> 00:58:50,694
Come on, Father. I mean, Mariano.

867
00:58:56,430 --> 00:58:58,487
[Isidoro]
Come on. The car is here.

868
00:58:59,530 --> 00:59:01,894
Father, they'll be safe. Don't worry.

869
00:59:02,005 --> 00:59:03,971
Father.

870
00:59:04,072 --> 00:59:05,504
[Pedro]
Come on!

871
00:59:05,606 --> 00:59:07,196
[Santiago]
I'll look after them. I promise.

872
00:59:07,305 --> 00:59:10,793
Come on! Father, come on.

873
00:59:10,905 --> 00:59:12,201
Hey, come on.

874
00:59:15,972 --> 00:59:18,938
- [Man] Stop! Stop!
- [Woman Crying]

875
00:59:19,039 --> 00:59:21,403
Come this way. Get the fat pig.

876
00:59:21,506 --> 00:59:23,233
Father! Father!

877
00:59:24,472 --> 00:59:26,404
[Man]
Oh! Oh! No!

878
00:59:28,305 --> 00:59:29,531
Come on! Come here.

879
00:59:29,638 --> 00:59:31,365
You stinking priest!

880
00:59:36,039 --> 00:59:38,596
- If you want, go ahead, pray.
- No.

881
00:59:39,638 --> 00:59:40,604
No! No!

882
00:59:43,338 --> 00:59:44,770
[Gasps]

883
00:59:44,872 --> 00:59:46,394
[Spits]

884
00:59:47,872 --> 00:59:49,701
Come on. Come on.

885
00:59:49,805 --> 00:59:52,270
- [Air-raid Siren Wailing]
- Come on.

886
00:59:53,204 --> 00:59:55,999
[Airplane Approaching]

887
00:59:56,104 --> 00:59:57,967
Get down! Get down!

888
00:59:59,138 --> 01:00:00,865
[Machine Gun Fire]

889
01:00:00,971 --> 01:00:03,267
- [Man] Lie down!
- [Woman Screams]

890
01:00:10,804 --> 01:00:13,362
- Swine!
- Not swine, Juan.

891
01:00:13,471 --> 01:00:15,993
- Men- like us.
- Men?

892
01:00:16,104 --> 01:00:19,627
Pedro, what did Father Lazaro
ever offer them but love?

893
01:00:19,737 --> 01:00:21,203
How could they do what they did?

894
01:00:21,304 --> 01:00:22,792
Because they see us as part of a system...

895
01:00:22,904 --> 01:00:25,301
- which causes them pain and despair.
- [Exhales]

896
01:00:25,404 --> 01:00:27,836
We- We have to pray.

897
01:00:28,771 --> 01:00:31,236
First for-for Father Lazaro...

898
01:00:31,337 --> 01:00:32,803
and then for his murderers.

899
01:00:32,904 --> 01:00:35,096
But they're murderers,
and they took pleasure in it.

900
01:00:35,203 --> 01:00:37,169
What do you want to do to those swine?

901
01:00:37,270 --> 01:00:40,134
Truthfully. Right now,
what do you want to do to them if you could?

902
01:00:40,237 --> 01:00:42,066
Truthfully.
And wouldn't you take pleasure in it?

903
01:00:47,704 --> 01:00:48,999
[Sniffles]

904
01:00:51,770 --> 01:00:53,464
[Crying]

905
01:00:57,570 --> 01:01:00,035
And yet we're no swine, are we?

906
01:01:00,137 --> 01:01:02,762
But it's not the same, Father.

907
01:01:02,870 --> 01:01:05,802
No human being- not one of us-

908
01:01:05,903 --> 01:01:07,369
is free from human weakness.

909
01:01:07,469 --> 01:01:08,435
No one.

910
01:01:10,337 --> 01:01:12,427
Our faith is a gift...

911
01:01:12,536 --> 01:01:16,025
and God has called us
to manifest it in love...

912
01:01:16,137 --> 01:01:17,932
here on earth.

913
01:01:18,037 --> 01:01:21,560
Unwavering love for every child of God,
no matter who it is.

914
01:01:21,669 --> 01:01:24,134
No matter what side,
no matter what circumstances.

915
01:01:24,236 --> 01:01:27,293
- Even if they are wrong?
- Yes, Juan!

916
01:01:27,403 --> 01:01:29,096
Even if they are wrong.

917
01:01:34,536 --> 01:01:37,468
You understand?

918
01:01:45,436 --> 01:01:47,901
[Sobbing]

919
01:02:04,335 --> 01:02:06,995
[Explosion]

920
01:02:07,668 --> 01:02:08,793
[Cord Snaps]

921
01:02:13,735 --> 01:02:15,428
Forgive us our trespasses.

922
01:02:17,168 --> 01:02:21,533
Forgive me, Lord, for my anger.

923
01:02:21,635 --> 01:02:24,226
For the anger of others.

924
01:02:24,335 --> 01:02:25,801
For hatred...

925
01:02:25,901 --> 01:02:28,231
and for those who are killing.

926
01:02:28,335 --> 01:02:30,426
Help me find strength.
[Groans]

927
01:02:32,734 --> 01:02:35,530
[Whipping Continues]

928
01:03:06,734 --> 01:03:08,290
I <i>Viva la Repúblical</i>

929
01:03:08,401 --> 01:03:10,333
[Crowd]
I <i>Vival</i>

930
01:03:10,434 --> 01:03:13,798
## [Singing In Spanish]

931
01:03:24,434 --> 01:03:26,763
Hey. Take a picture of this.

932
01:03:26,867 --> 01:03:28,094
[Photographer]
Of course.

933
01:03:31,200 --> 01:03:32,563
[Shutter Clicks]

934
01:03:32,666 --> 01:03:34,360
Thank you, Captain. Let's go.

935
01:03:34,467 --> 01:03:36,228
[Lldiko]
He's going to put me in the book.

936
01:03:36,334 --> 01:03:40,663
Well, better to be put in a song.

937
01:03:40,767 --> 01:03:42,357
I read hundreds of books in jail...

938
01:03:42,466 --> 01:03:44,455
and I only liked <i>Crime and Punishment.</i>

939
01:03:44,566 --> 01:03:47,589
[Laughs]
I haven't read many books.

940
01:03:49,134 --> 01:03:51,100
Then how do you know what life has to offer?

941
01:03:52,967 --> 01:03:54,694
I dream.

942
01:03:56,066 --> 01:03:57,555
So do I.

943
01:04:01,166 --> 01:04:03,064
[Man]
I<i>Abajo los tiranosl</i>

944
01:04:03,166 --> 01:04:06,132
i<i>Abajo los burguesesl</i>

945
01:04:06,233 --> 01:04:09,757
[Cheering]

946
01:04:20,799 --> 01:04:22,493
[Man]
I <i>Viva la Repúblical</i>

947
01:04:22,599 --> 01:04:24,429
i <i>Vival</i>

948
01:04:24,532 --> 01:04:26,055
[Man]
I <i>Viva la anarquíal</i>

949
01:04:26,166 --> 01:04:27,859
i <i>Vival</i>

950
01:04:29,532 --> 01:04:31,691
[Exclaiming, Shouting]

951
01:04:38,932 --> 01:04:40,898
[Man Shouting]

952
01:04:46,532 --> 01:04:49,692
Tonight when we camp, I want to come to you.

953
01:04:49,799 --> 01:04:51,389
No, Manolo. I have told you.

954
01:04:51,499 --> 01:04:53,362
Why not?

955
01:04:53,465 --> 01:04:55,727
Why put yourself through this?

956
01:04:55,831 --> 01:04:57,627
You give yourself to Oriol.

957
01:04:58,931 --> 01:05:00,420
So I choose.

958
01:05:00,532 --> 01:05:02,464
And you have with others.
I know.

959
01:05:05,499 --> 01:05:08,021
Because they might die at any moment!

960
01:05:08,132 --> 01:05:10,962
It is my choice
if I wish to give them comfort.

961
01:05:13,065 --> 01:05:15,656
Then why refuse me?

962
01:05:15,765 --> 01:05:17,788
Because jealousy's ugly.

963
01:05:19,464 --> 01:05:21,487
- Ildiko, listen.
- I saw it in your face...

964
01:05:21,598 --> 01:05:24,564
when we first met during Oriol's speech.

965
01:05:24,664 --> 01:05:26,357
You'd rather be him than you.

966
01:05:52,964 --> 01:05:55,556
[Airplane Passing Overhead]

967
01:05:57,663 --> 01:05:59,095
<i>Nyetl Nyetl Nyetl</i>

968
01:06:02,131 --> 01:06:04,494
[Soldiers Speaking Russian]

969
01:06:11,797 --> 01:06:14,786
[Morse Code]

970
01:06:17,363 --> 01:06:19,226
[Airplane Passing Overhead]

971
01:06:25,697 --> 01:06:28,492
[Man]
Come on, you lot! Come on! Wake!

972
01:06:28,597 --> 01:06:30,495
[Man <i>#2</i>]
I've been sleeping under the sky!

973
01:06:33,463 --> 01:06:35,429
- [Explosion In Distance]
- [Men Shouting]

974
01:06:38,196 --> 01:06:39,889
Here. God bless you.

975
01:06:45,597 --> 01:06:48,495
Thank you, Isidoro.
This was very brave of you.

976
01:06:53,763 --> 01:06:57,252
We'll celebrate Mass at 1:<i>00</i>,
and I'll hear confessions at 3:<i>00</i>.

977
01:06:57,363 --> 01:06:59,022
- [Exhales] Sorry, Father, but-
- Don't worry.

978
01:06:59,130 --> 01:07:00,823
I know the perfect place.

979
01:07:00,929 --> 01:07:03,588
- ## [Accordion: Folk]
- [Elephants Trumpeting]

980
01:07:03,696 --> 01:07:06,526
<i>... ego te absolvo a peccatis tuis...</i>

981
01:07:06,629 --> 01:07:09,118
<i>in nomine Patris et Filii et Spiritus Sancti.</i>

982
01:07:09,229 --> 01:07:11,752
Thank you, Father.

983
01:07:11,863 --> 01:07:13,954
- ## [Continues]
- [Ducks Quacking]

984
01:07:26,462 --> 01:07:29,121
Bless me, Father, for I have sinned.

985
01:07:29,229 --> 01:07:31,990
My last confession was five months ago.

986
01:07:32,095 --> 01:07:34,254
And I promise that-

987
01:07:36,795 --> 01:07:38,727
Father.

988
01:07:39,728 --> 01:07:41,024
Papers.

989
01:08:00,495 --> 01:08:02,393
Enjoying the zoo, are we?

990
01:08:02,495 --> 01:08:06,257
Yes. It's very educational.

991
01:08:06,361 --> 01:08:10,521
And where is the wife
when you're being <i>educated?</i>

992
01:08:10,628 --> 01:08:13,719
Back home doing the laundry?
[Laughing]

993
01:08:19,827 --> 01:08:21,191
[Sighs]

994
01:08:24,028 --> 01:08:25,789
My mother's idea.

995
01:08:25,894 --> 01:08:28,190
It's not the first time it's kept me safe.

996
01:08:32,395 --> 01:08:33,860
Father, do you need shelter?

997
01:08:36,128 --> 01:08:38,355
Yes. Do you know somewhere?

998
01:08:39,560 --> 01:08:41,389
Well, I only have a single room...

999
01:08:41,494 --> 01:08:44,483
and there's almost no room for me, but if-

1000
01:08:44,594 --> 01:08:46,287
You are beautiful.

1001
01:08:47,527 --> 01:08:51,459
I am a priest, but- but also a man.

1002
01:08:54,160 --> 01:08:56,820
So I thank you for your courage...

1003
01:08:56,927 --> 01:08:58,552
but no.

1004
01:09:14,360 --> 01:09:17,326
## [Guitar: Folk]

1005
01:09:19,494 --> 01:09:22,426
[Man Chattering]

1006
01:09:32,459 --> 01:09:35,187
Oriol, what is it?

1007
01:09:42,693 --> 01:09:45,352
If something happens to me...

1008
01:09:48,026 --> 01:09:49,788
I'll wait for you on the other side.

1009
01:09:49,893 --> 01:09:53,847
- Don't say that.
- We are at war, lldiko. I don't know.

1010
01:09:55,426 --> 01:09:57,722
We've held the fascists back for two years.

1011
01:09:59,393 --> 01:10:02,052
But the Germans give them planes...

1012
01:10:02,159 --> 01:10:05,455
and our leaders in Madrid
fight amongst themselves...

1013
01:10:05,559 --> 01:10:07,024
and give us nothing.

1014
01:10:07,126 --> 01:10:11,615
So let's dream now... while we can.

1015
01:10:27,692 --> 01:10:30,658
[Morse Code Tapping]

1016
01:11:12,991 --> 01:11:14,718
[Man]
We need a stretcher!

1017
01:11:16,190 --> 01:11:18,213
[Man]
Here they come again!

1018
01:11:19,824 --> 01:11:23,449
- [Groaning]
- Help! Help!

1019
01:11:24,824 --> 01:11:27,585
- [Man] Ammunition!
- [Airplane Engines Buzzing]

1020
01:11:27,691 --> 01:11:29,623
[Screaming]

1021
01:11:29,724 --> 01:11:32,713
The bastards know exactly where to find us.

1022
01:11:32,824 --> 01:11:35,722
Squeeze! Squeeze!

1023
01:11:36,890 --> 01:11:38,220
[Woman]
Let me take care of that.

1024
01:11:38,324 --> 01:11:40,222
No, leave it. Come on. Let's go.

1025
01:11:40,324 --> 01:11:42,449
Let's go, let's go!

1026
01:11:49,890 --> 01:11:51,947
This stinks.

1027
01:11:52,057 --> 01:11:54,648
We're sitting ducks.

1028
01:11:54,757 --> 01:11:57,280
Those damn communists in Madrid
are hanging us out to dry.

1029
01:11:58,556 --> 01:12:01,045
We're being sacrificed.

1030
01:12:03,957 --> 01:12:05,422
[Manolo]
I can do something about that.

1031
01:12:10,790 --> 01:12:13,187
What's that then?

1032
01:12:13,289 --> 01:12:15,016
A safe-conduct.

1033
01:12:15,123 --> 01:12:16,885
It's a pass.

1034
01:12:16,989 --> 01:12:21,046
It allows anyone safe passage
to the enemy side.

1035
01:12:21,289 --> 01:12:24,153
## [People Singing Hymn Quietly]

1036
01:12:27,656 --> 01:12:31,088
[Saying Mass In Latin]

1037
01:12:39,922 --> 01:12:41,218
Let's go!

1038
01:12:42,622 --> 01:12:44,952
- Open the gate!
- [Man] Coming! I'm coming!

1039
01:12:45,056 --> 01:12:48,113
The militia! The militia are here!

1040
01:12:48,223 --> 01:12:50,518
- Come with me! Come with me!
- Quickly! This way!

1041
01:13:00,489 --> 01:13:01,955
Jorge, get out.

1042
01:13:02,055 --> 01:13:03,316
What the hell is going on?

1043
01:13:03,422 --> 01:13:04,786
We need to hide the priest.

1044
01:13:04,889 --> 01:13:05,912
Priest?

1045
01:13:06,022 --> 01:13:07,921
The militia are here. They'll kill him.

1046
01:13:08,022 --> 01:13:10,045
- Good riddance.
- Slob.

1047
01:13:10,155 --> 01:13:11,950
Come on. Go. Please go. Quickly. Go.

1048
01:13:12,055 --> 01:13:13,078
Priest.

1049
01:13:13,188 --> 01:13:15,746
What if I turn you in?

1050
01:13:15,855 --> 01:13:19,049
Then I'll meet my Maker
far sooner than anticipated.

1051
01:13:19,155 --> 01:13:21,246
If they find you here, so will I.

1052
01:13:21,355 --> 01:13:23,184
Yes, you're right.
Isidoro, stay here and hide.

1053
01:13:23,288 --> 01:13:24,810
- No, Father. Please.
- I will give myself up.

1054
01:13:24,921 --> 01:13:26,387
- I will give myself up.
- [Isidoro] No.

1055
01:13:26,489 --> 01:13:27,886
[Glass Shatters]

1056
01:13:27,988 --> 01:13:29,647
- [Soldier] Get your papers! Now!
- They're coming!

1057
01:13:29,755 --> 01:13:32,119
Begone! Go!

1058
01:13:33,454 --> 01:13:36,250
[Soldiers Shouting]

1059
01:13:44,287 --> 01:13:45,753
Your papers.

1060
01:13:46,654 --> 01:13:48,483
In my jacket.

1061
01:13:48,588 --> 01:13:50,884
Then get them.

1062
01:13:50,988 --> 01:13:51,612
Ana.

1063
01:13:56,821 --> 01:13:58,286
[Soldier]
Look in there.

1064
01:14:14,021 --> 01:14:15,487
[Whispers]

1065
01:14:18,221 --> 01:14:19,777
Miguel.

1066
01:14:32,054 --> 01:14:33,679
[Handle Clattering]

1067
01:14:37,887 --> 01:14:39,352
Where's the key?

1068
01:14:49,020 --> 01:14:51,384
Where's the key, <i>sir?</i>

1069
01:15:07,053 --> 01:15:10,417
Captain, sir. Forgive me, sir.

1070
01:15:12,919 --> 01:15:15,749
Don't worry. Just doing your duty.

1071
01:15:22,953 --> 01:15:23,919
[Sighs]

1072
01:15:24,020 --> 01:15:26,508
[Shouting Continues]

1073
01:15:32,085 --> 01:15:33,278
They've gone.

1074
01:15:33,386 --> 01:15:35,215
You better stay here until it gets dark.

1075
01:15:35,319 --> 01:15:37,080
Then get the hell out of Madrid...

1076
01:15:37,185 --> 01:15:38,879
unless you've got a death wish.

1077
01:15:38,985 --> 01:15:40,815
Thank you.

1078
01:15:40,918 --> 01:15:42,612
Thank you?

1079
01:15:42,719 --> 01:15:44,617
They should put me in a madhouse.

1080
01:15:48,386 --> 01:15:50,614
<i>##[Guitar... Folk]</i>

1081
01:15:55,718 --> 01:15:59,582
I have a straitjacket
if you think he'll be dangerous.

1082
01:15:59,685 --> 01:16:01,674
Don't worry. He'll be fine.

1083
01:16:03,518 --> 01:16:05,677
<i>##[Man Singing Folk]</i>

1084
01:16:12,551 --> 01:16:16,483
Oh, no. There's militia there.
There's a roadblock.

1085
01:16:16,585 --> 01:16:17,744
Please, sir, turn left.

1086
01:16:17,852 --> 01:16:20,477
<i>##[Continues]</i>

1087
01:16:28,018 --> 01:16:32,610
God is a primitive concept
we grew out of during the Enlightenment!

1088
01:16:32,718 --> 01:16:34,047
Shh! Shh, shh!

1089
01:16:34,151 --> 01:16:37,174
[Patients Chattering, Shouting]

1090
01:16:37,284 --> 01:16:39,341
[Explosions]

1091
01:16:39,451 --> 01:16:41,848
[Laughing]

1092
01:16:41,951 --> 01:16:45,111
[Cheering, Clamoring]

1093
01:16:45,218 --> 01:16:46,514
[Man]
Who'll dare fight me?

1094
01:16:46,617 --> 01:16:49,845
Huh? Who? Who will dare fight me?

1095
01:16:49,951 --> 01:16:52,042
- Who?
- [Whistle Blowing]

1096
01:16:52,151 --> 01:16:54,014
Who will dare fight me?

1097
01:16:54,118 --> 01:16:55,447
[Airplanes Passing Overhead]

1098
01:16:56,884 --> 01:16:57,747
[Whistle Blowing]

1099
01:16:57,851 --> 01:17:00,942
[Banging On Pots, Pans]

1100
01:17:12,717 --> 01:17:15,911
You bastards! You enjoy this!

1101
01:17:16,950 --> 01:17:19,473
[Groaning]

1102
01:17:24,250 --> 01:17:27,011
Someone is betraying us, and, I swear...

1103
01:17:27,117 --> 01:17:30,083
when I find out who it is- no mercy.

1104
01:17:42,549 --> 01:17:44,243
We have to do it tonight.

1105
01:17:46,683 --> 01:17:49,081
[Explosions]

1106
01:17:55,716 --> 01:18:00,273
He doesn't hear you, does he?

1107
01:18:05,216 --> 01:18:08,774
All this pain, and God just stays silent.

1108
01:18:12,082 --> 01:18:14,048
He is a monster, you know?

1109
01:18:25,949 --> 01:18:27,415
I love him.

1110
01:18:32,049 --> 01:18:33,605
Although he's a monster?

1111
01:18:33,715 --> 01:18:35,181
[Chuckles]

1112
01:18:37,382 --> 01:18:39,348
Women can love monsters.

1113
01:18:47,615 --> 01:18:49,672
This is the address! Dismount!

1114
01:18:55,181 --> 01:18:56,647
[Knocking On Door]

1115
01:18:57,648 --> 01:18:59,375
Isidoro, we need to change plans.

1116
01:19:01,715 --> 01:19:03,408
We're here to search the building.

1117
01:19:03,515 --> 01:19:07,913
After I was raped, I stopped going to Mass.

1118
01:19:08,015 --> 01:19:11,879
I couldn't understand
how God allowed such a thing.

1119
01:19:13,681 --> 01:19:18,704
I accepted, you see, God can be terrible.

1120
01:19:20,115 --> 01:19:21,740
So now I do go to Mass...

1121
01:19:21,848 --> 01:19:26,281
and my prayers are deeper than before.

1122
01:19:27,948 --> 01:19:29,675
I fight him with love, you see.

1123
01:19:35,280 --> 01:19:36,576
I like you.

1124
01:19:40,881 --> 01:19:42,506
You look me in the eye.

1125
01:19:42,614 --> 01:19:46,307
- You don't pity me.
- No.

1126
01:19:48,114 --> 01:19:50,012
No, you are extremely brave.

1127
01:19:50,114 --> 01:19:52,080
Not really.

1128
01:19:54,913 --> 01:19:57,902
I still sleep with the lights on...

1129
01:19:58,014 --> 01:20:00,003
and a chair wedged under the door handle.

1130
01:20:06,147 --> 01:20:08,136
I think you have mountains to climb.

1131
01:20:10,214 --> 01:20:12,271
And I think it will be painful.

1132
01:20:13,713 --> 01:20:17,237
But that will make it seem sweet
when you are finished.

1133
01:20:18,380 --> 01:20:20,369
- [Door Opens]
- [Men Shouting]

1134
01:20:20,480 --> 01:20:23,241
Father. Father.

1135
01:20:23,346 --> 01:20:24,972
- We have to leave.
- [Shouting Continues]

1136
01:20:25,080 --> 01:20:27,170
[Grunts]
Where to this time?

1137
01:20:27,279 --> 01:20:30,370
Uh, over the Pyrenees.

1138
01:20:30,480 --> 01:20:31,776
- [Man Shouting] Come back here!
- No.

1139
01:20:31,880 --> 01:20:33,209
- We'll be safe there.
- No!

1140
01:20:33,313 --> 01:20:35,677
I'm going back into the city.

1141
01:20:35,780 --> 01:20:38,337
I promised God his flock here
would never be deserted.

1142
01:20:38,446 --> 01:20:40,605
- I'm not going to Andorra.
- No.

1143
01:20:40,713 --> 01:20:43,110
No, it's suicide to stay, and you know it.

1144
01:20:43,213 --> 01:20:44,872
And if you die, they <i>will</i> be deserted.

1145
01:20:44,979 --> 01:20:46,945
And Carmen and your mother
and Santiago-

1146
01:20:47,046 --> 01:20:48,342
- Father.
- [Shouting Continues]

1147
01:20:48,446 --> 01:20:50,275
- No.
- We have to leave.

1148
01:20:51,612 --> 01:20:53,101
Yes, please.

1149
01:20:58,812 --> 01:21:00,335
Over the mountains?

1150
01:21:01,146 --> 01:21:02,169
Yeah.

1151
01:21:05,479 --> 01:21:07,411
Father?

1152
01:21:09,812 --> 01:21:12,176
<i>- [Thunder Rumbling]</i>
- [Chattering]

1153
01:21:23,145 --> 01:21:26,043
Commandant, it's field three, sir.

1154
01:21:26,145 --> 01:21:28,134
He says this is his last transmission.

1155
01:21:32,811 --> 01:21:35,243
Sir, we've lost our mole.

1156
01:21:41,678 --> 01:21:45,372
<i>[Radio Static Crackling]</i>

1157
01:21:54,112 --> 01:21:58,271
<i>[Manolo Narrating]</i>
<i>Slaying your demons is never easy.</i>

1158
01:21:58,378 --> 01:22:02,640
<i>Sometimes it's better</i>
<i>to get someone else to slay them for you.</i>

1159
01:22:15,011 --> 01:22:17,307
- [Footsteps Approaching]
- [Soldier] Get up! Get her up!

1160
01:22:17,411 --> 01:22:19,468
- [Gasps]
- [Grunting]

1161
01:22:19,578 --> 01:22:21,805
- [Grunts]
- [Gasps]

1162
01:22:21,910 --> 01:22:24,274
Look at this! Look at this!

1163
01:22:25,311 --> 01:22:26,970
- What is this?
<i>- [Static Crackling]</i>

1164
01:22:27,077 --> 01:22:28,634
- It's a radio!
- [Shatters]

1165
01:22:28,744 --> 01:22:31,801
Come on! Come on! You filthy traitor!

1166
01:22:31,910 --> 01:22:33,376
- [Murmuring In Spanish]
- [Grunts]

1167
01:22:33,478 --> 01:22:34,943
[Soldier <i>#2</i>]
They found the traitor!

1168
01:22:35,044 --> 01:22:37,306
[Clamoring]

1169
01:22:37,411 --> 01:22:39,899
Are you sure? Who saw them? Who?

1170
01:22:40,011 --> 01:22:41,806
Everyone! Them!

1171
01:22:41,910 --> 01:22:43,967
Stop! Hey!

1172
01:22:44,077 --> 01:22:45,542
[Clamoring Stops]

1173
01:22:45,643 --> 01:22:47,234
Let's take a vote!

1174
01:22:48,677 --> 01:22:50,939
Who wants to kill her?

1175
01:22:51,044 --> 01:22:53,271
[Crowd Shouts]

1176
01:22:55,744 --> 01:22:57,403
What more?

1177
01:22:58,343 --> 01:22:59,809
[Sighs]

1178
01:22:59,910 --> 01:23:01,170
I will do it.

1179
01:23:01,276 --> 01:23:02,572
What?

1180
01:23:05,477 --> 01:23:06,942
I will do it.

1181
01:23:33,676 --> 01:23:35,142
[Rustling]

1182
01:23:43,542 --> 01:23:45,804
How could you have done this?

1183
01:23:45,909 --> 01:23:47,932
I didn't, Oriol.

1184
01:23:48,043 --> 01:23:49,508
Five men say they saw you.

1185
01:23:49,609 --> 01:23:52,006
- And they're lying.
- But you were found with the radio.

1186
01:23:52,109 --> 01:23:55,007
It was planted.
For God's sake, isn't it obvious?

1187
01:23:55,942 --> 01:23:57,067
No.

1188
01:23:58,776 --> 01:24:00,332
You're Hungarian.

1189
01:24:00,442 --> 01:24:03,067
And there are Hungarians
fighting with the fascists too.

1190
01:24:06,442 --> 01:24:08,499
They were going to kill you themselves.

1191
01:24:15,175 --> 01:24:16,731
But I said I would do it.

1192
01:24:27,608 --> 01:24:29,665
When I was 18...

1193
01:24:29,775 --> 01:24:31,673
I killed a political boss.

1194
01:24:32,942 --> 01:24:35,237
And I was proud of it.

1195
01:24:36,842 --> 01:24:40,035
But now-
[Sniffling]

1196
01:24:40,141 --> 01:24:42,733
What I have to do ma- makes me feel sick.

1197
01:24:44,775 --> 01:24:47,070
I loved you, lldiko.

1198
01:24:47,174 --> 01:24:49,003
But your kisses came from the lips of Judas.

1199
01:24:49,108 --> 01:24:52,006
[Sobbing]
No! No! No, please!

1200
01:24:52,108 --> 01:24:54,767
- How many have died because of you?
- [Sobbing]

1201
01:24:54,874 --> 01:24:57,170
- How many?
- Please!

1202
01:24:57,274 --> 01:24:59,467
Because I trusted you.

1203
01:24:59,575 --> 01:25:02,097
[Sobbing]

1204
01:25:02,208 --> 01:25:05,436
[Sobbing Continues]

1205
01:25:05,540 --> 01:25:06,506
- [Screams]
- [Gunshot]

1206
01:25:06,607 --> 01:25:07,903
Lldiko.

1207
01:25:12,028 --> 01:25:16,051
[Groaning]

1208
01:25:16,161 --> 01:25:19,649
[Ringing]

1209
01:25:20,828 --> 01:25:22,350
Hello?

1210
01:25:22,461 --> 01:25:24,121
Yeah.

1211
01:25:26,794 --> 01:25:28,089
Ah.

1212
01:25:31,027 --> 01:25:32,254
Thanks.

1213
01:25:35,160 --> 01:25:37,058
It's Dad.

1214
01:25:37,160 --> 01:25:39,251
He's been taken to hospital.

1215
01:25:39,494 --> 01:25:42,982
- [Monitor Beeping]
- [Respirator Hissing]

1216
01:25:54,494 --> 01:25:58,392
[Lldiko Screaming]

1217
01:25:59,894 --> 01:26:03,348
[Screaming, Sobbing]

1218
01:26:10,260 --> 01:26:13,022
What do we do now?

1219
01:26:13,127 --> 01:26:14,820
- Get the men away from here.
- How?

1220
01:26:14,927 --> 01:26:18,018
- [Sobbing Continues]
- Tell them he was a traitor.
He was guilty. He shot himself.

1221
01:26:18,126 --> 01:26:19,422
They won't believe it.

1222
01:26:19,527 --> 01:26:21,049
- They will!
- No-

1223
01:26:21,159 --> 01:26:22,785
- They saw it themselves.
- [Lldiko Screaming]

1224
01:26:22,894 --> 01:26:25,018
- They trust you. Go!
- [Screaming Continues]

1225
01:26:25,126 --> 01:26:26,649
Go!

1226
01:26:26,760 --> 01:26:29,521
[Screaming, Sobbing Continue]

1227
01:26:29,627 --> 01:26:32,854
- Come on!
- [Sobbing Continues]

1228
01:26:34,226 --> 01:26:36,783
- [Sobbing Continues]
- [Man Shouting, Indistinct]

1229
01:26:39,026 --> 01:26:41,856
[Man]
Come on! Get those trucks moving!

1230
01:26:41,959 --> 01:26:45,187
Get loaded up!
Don't leave anything behind! Come on!

1231
01:26:45,293 --> 01:26:48,918
[Crying]

1232
01:27:00,492 --> 01:27:02,355
[Crying Continues]

1233
01:27:05,559 --> 01:27:07,752
Who would have thought...

1234
01:27:07,859 --> 01:27:09,825
that someone like you-

1235
01:27:12,492 --> 01:27:15,856
someone like you could have
destroyed someone like him?

1236
01:27:15,958 --> 01:27:19,322
[Sobbing]
Someone like you.

1237
01:27:19,425 --> 01:27:21,755
[Sobbing, Panting]

1238
01:27:24,626 --> 01:27:26,615
This is yours!

1239
01:27:31,825 --> 01:27:33,086
Where are you going?

1240
01:27:33,192 --> 01:27:36,215
[Vomits, Coughs]

1241
01:27:49,491 --> 01:27:51,048
You should go back to Madrid.

1242
01:27:52,125 --> 01:27:53,420
I can arrange it.

1243
01:28:00,691 --> 01:28:02,156
For the baby's sake!

1244
01:28:29,091 --> 01:28:31,556
Hey! Where are you going! Hey!

1245
01:28:31,657 --> 01:28:34,851
Let her go. I found this on his body.

1246
01:28:34,957 --> 01:28:38,286
It's a safe-conduct.
A pass... from the enemy.

1247
01:28:46,724 --> 01:28:48,519
He's right.

1248
01:28:48,624 --> 01:28:51,055
[Spits]
Let her go. Let her go!

1249
01:28:51,156 --> 01:28:52,782
- Let her go.
- Give her the gun.

1250
01:29:08,723 --> 01:29:10,814
[Whispering]
Manolo, what about us?

1251
01:29:10,923 --> 01:29:12,980
What about us?

1252
01:29:13,090 --> 01:29:15,715
You have your passes. Use them.

1253
01:29:22,823 --> 01:29:24,812
[Leila]
He's dying, Robbie.

1254
01:29:24,923 --> 01:29:28,582
You have to get over this thing between you-
for both our sakes.

